en: RG: Wouldn’t put it past Mum. You know she’s been obsessing over who I should marry since the day I was born. She drives me CRAZY with it. You’re so lucky.

en: “Well then, let’s ground you.” The guru led his acolyte down the steps of the pavilion onto the dewy grass, and they sat facing each other in lotus position.
Sesotho: "Ho lokile, a re ke re o theohe." ʻO ka ʻenehana hoʻoholo ʻana i ka ʻenehana hoʻoholo ʻana i ka ʻenehana ʻana i ka loli.
Yorùbá: "O dara lẹhinna, jẹ ki a fi ọ silẹ." Ọ̀jọ̀gbọ́n náà darí acolyte rẹ̀ sọ̀kalẹ̀ ní àwọn ìpele gbọ̀ngàn náà sí orí koríko ìrì, wọ́n sì jókòó kọjú sí ara wọn ní ipò lotus.
Setswana (Tswana): "Ok, lets go ground." Ba ne ba isiwa kwa godimo ga bojang jo bo kwa godimo, mme ba ne ba nna ba ntse ba lebagana le loruo.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): Na reira ïa, e hi'opo'a ana'e tatou ia oe ". Ua arata'i atura te gourou i to'na pereoo i raro i te mau taahiraa o te mato i ni'a i te aihere hau, e ua parahi a'era raua i mua i te tahi e te tahi i ni'a i te parahiraa.
Maithili: "ठीक अछि तखन, चलू अहां के जमीन पर लए लिय।" गुरु अपन एकोलाइटकेँ मंडपक सीढ़ीसँ नीचाँ ओस भरल घास पर लऽ गेलाह, आ ओ सभ कमलक स्थितिमे एक दोसराक सम्मुख बैसल छलाह।
Malagasy: "Noho izany, andao hiorina amin'ny tany." Notarihin'ilay guru nidina ny tohatra tao amin'ilay tranoeva ho any amin'ny bozaka ando izy, ary nipetraka nifanatrika teo amin'ny toerana nisy ny lotus izy ireo.
Divehi (Dhivehi): "އެހެންވީމަ ލެޓްސް ގްރައުންޑް ޔޫ." ގުރުއާން އޭނާގެ އެކޮލައިޓް ޕެވިލިއަންގެ ސިޑިން ފައިބައިގެން ޑިއު ގްރާސްގެ މައްޗަށް ގެންގޮސް އެކަކު އަނެކަކާ ކުރިމަތިލައިގެން ލޮޓަސް ޕޮޒިޝަންގައި އިށީނެވެ.

en: “Your rage cannot hurt you. Just visualize that rage as a little red ball, a red ball that is spinning from your crown chakra, through your heart chakra, through your solar plexus, and out your base chakra. Exhale fully and just let the ball flow through you from top to bottom, top to bottom…”
Sesotho: Khalefo ea hao e ke ke ea u utloisa bohloko. Ho bona feela hore bohale joalo ka bolo e khubelu e khubelu, bolo e khubelu e tsoang ho chakra ea hau ea moqhaka, ka pelo ea hau chakra, ka plexus ea hau ea letsatsi, le ho tsoa chakra ea hau ea mantlha. Exhale ka botlalo 'me feela lumella bolo e phalla ho uena ho tloha holimo ho ea tlaase, holimo ho ea tlase ...
Yorùbá: "Ibinu rẹ ko le ṣe ipalara fun ọ. Kàn fojú inú wo ìbínú yẹn gẹ́gẹ́ bí bọ́ọ̀lù pupa díẹ̀, bọ́ọ̀lù pupa tí ó ń yí láti orí adé rẹ chakra, nípasẹ̀ ọkàn rẹ chakra, nípasẹ̀ plexus oòrùn rẹ, àti láti ìpìlẹ̀ rẹ chakra. Exhale ni kikun ati ki o kan jẹ ki rogodo ṣàn nipasẹ rẹ lati oke si isalẹ, oke si isalẹ ..."

'O ne a gôga go tswa kwa godimo go ya kwa godimo go ya kwa tlase' - Let the ball flow through through you from top to bottom

en: “Did I have a transient ischemic stroke? I’m absolutely convinced I did. You have no idea what happened in the middle of the night!”
Sesotho: Na ke ne ke na le transient ischemic stroke? Ke kholisehile ka botlalo hore ke entse joalo. Ha u tsebe se etsahetseng har'a mpa ea bosiu. "
Yorùbá: Ṣé mo ní àrùn kẹ́míkà ìgbà díẹ̀? Ó dá mi lójú pé mo ṣe é. O kò mọ ohun tó ṣẹlẹ̀ ní àárín òru!"
Setswana (Tswana): A ke ne ke na le bolwetse jo bo sa re tshwanelang jwa go idiba? Ke ne ke tlhomamisegile gore ke ne ka dira jalo. Ga ke itse gore ke eng se o se batlang masigo o sa se bone motshegare."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Ua roohia anei au i te ma'i mafatu tupu taue? Ua papû roa ia'u e, ua na reira vau. Aita oe i ite eaha tei tupu i te tuiraa pô !
Maithili: "की हमरा क्षणिक इस्कीमिक स्ट्रोक भेल? हम बिल्कुल आश्वस्त छी जे हम केलहुं। अहां के पता नहि अछि जे मध्यरात्रि मे की भेल!"

en: “You don’t get it. A volcano basically erupted at the wedding site! The Balinese pavilion, the replica of the bar at Loulou’s, the ballroom mimicking the checkerboard floors at Château d’Anet, it’s all ruined! Everything has been ruined!”
Sesotho: "Ha u e fumane. Ha e le hantle seretse se chesang se ile sa thunya sebakeng sa lenyalo! Pavilion ea Balinese, replica ea bareng e Loulou, ballroom e etsisa mekato ea checkerboard château d'Anet, tsohle li senyehile! Ntho e 'ngoe le e' ngoe e se e senyehile! "
Yorùbá: "O ko gba o. Òkè ńlá kan bú jáde ní ibi ìgbéyàwó! Gbọ̀ngàn Balinese, ẹ̀dà ilé-ọtí náà ní Loulou's, yàrá ìdárayá náà ń ṣe àgbékalẹ̀ àwọn ilẹ̀ checkerboard ní Château d'Anet, gbogbo rẹ̀ ti bàjẹ́! Ohun gbogbo ti bajẹ! "
Setswana (Tswana): "Ok ya lo se. 13.1.1 1.1 1.1 1.1 1 2.1 1.2 1 ʻO ke kʻoluʻoluʻo o ka ʻele! "Dilo tse tsotlhe di a senyega!"
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Eita e roaa ia oe. Ua paaina te hoê mou'a auahi i te vahi faaipoiporaa! Te fare inuraa Balinese, te hoho'a o te fare inuraa i Loulou's, te piha hautiraa popo e taora ra i te mau tahua i raro i te fenua i Château d'Anet, ua ino roa ïa! Ua ino roa te mau mea atoa!"
Maithili: "अहां के इ नहि भेटत। मूल रूप सं विवाह स्थल पर एकटा ज्वालामुखी फूटल! बाली मंडप, लौलौ के बार के प्रतिकृति, चेटरबोर्ड के फर्श के नकल करय वाला बॉलरूम चेटौ डी'एनेट, ई सब बर्बाद भऽ गेल अछि! सब किछु बर्बाद भए गेल अछि!
Malagasy: "Tsy azonao izany. Nisy volkano nipoaka teo amin'ny toerana fampakaram - bady! Ny trano heva Balinese, ny dika mitovy amin'ny bara ao Loulou's, ny efitrano fandihizana maka tahaka ny gorodona ao Château d'Anet, rava avokoa izany rehetra izany! Potika daholo ny zava-drehetra!"
Divehi (Dhivehi): "ކަލެއަކަށް ނުލިބޭ. މައިގަނޑު ގޮތެއްގައި އަލިފާން ފަރުބަދައެއް ގޮއްވާލީ ކައިވެނީގެ ސަރަހައްދުގައި! ބެލިނީސް ޕެވިލިއަން، ލޫލޫގެ ބާގެ ރެޕްލިކާ، ޗެޓޫ ޑި އެނެޓްގެ ޗެކަރބޯޑް ފްލޯތައް ނަކަލުކުރާ ބޯލްރޫމް، މި ހުރިހާ ކަމެއް ހަލާކުވެއްޖެ! ހުރިހާ ކަމެއް ހަލާކުވެއްޖެ!"

en: *6 Let’s be clear, the signs of an actual stroke may include these sudden symptoms: facial drooping on one side of the face, arm weakness, and speech difficulty. Unless there is a kindly doctor next door whom your butler can quickly summon, please call your emergency medical service immediately if you experience these symptoms.
Sesotho: * 6 Ha re hlakiseng, lipontšo tsa stroke ea 'nete li ka kenyelletsa matšoao ana a tšohanyetso: sefahleho sa sefahleho ka lehlakoreng le leng la sefahleho, bofokoli ba letsoho le bothata ba ho bua. Ntle le haeba ho na le ngaka e mosa monyako o latelang eo butler oa hau a ka e bitsang kapele, ka kopo letsetsa ts'ebeletso ea hau ea bongaka ea tšohanyetso hang-hang haeba u na le matšoao ana.
Yorùbá: * 6 Jẹ ki a ṣe kedere, awọn ami ti ikolu gangan le pẹlu awọn aami aisan lojiji wọnyi: oju drooping ni ẹgbẹ kan ti oju, ailagbara apa, ati iṣoro ọrọ. Àyàfi tí dókítà onínúure bá wà ní ẹ̀gbẹ́ ilé tí òṣìṣẹ́ rẹ lè tètè pè, jọ̀wọ́ pe iṣẹ́ ìṣègùn pàjáwìrì rẹ lẹ́sẹ̀kẹsẹ̀ tí o bá ní ìrírí àwọn àmì wọ̀nyí.
Setswana (Tswana): 6 A re tlhaloseng, matshwao a sekgoreletsi sa mmatota a ka akaretsa matshwao ano a tshoganyetso: sefatlhego se se mo letlhakoreng le lengwe la sefatlhego, bokoa jwa letsogo le bothata jwa go bua. Ntle le fa go na le ngaka e e latelang e o ka e bitsang ka bonako, tsweetswee founela tirelo ya gago ya kalafi ya tshoganyetso ka bonako fa o itemogela matshwao ano.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): *6 Ia papu maitai ia tatou, te vai ra i roto i te mau tapao o te mauraa o te roro teie mau tapao o te tupu taue noa mai: te hoho'a mata e tahe ra i te hoê pae o te hoho'a mata, te paruparu o te rima, e te fifi o te paraparauraa. en: “Shush, it’s perfect. It was my great-grandmother’s. The San Francisco one who replenished all the coffers with her railroad money. Now Mummy will scold me for letting you wear it and forget what she really wants to scold me about.”
Sesotho: "Hahahahaha, that's perfect. E ne e le taba ea nkhono oa ka e moholo. San Francisco ea ileng a tlatsa coffers tsohle ka chelete ea hae ea seporo. Joale 'Mè oa ka o ile a nkopa hore ke e tlole, 'me u lebale seo a batlang ho mpolella sona. "

en: “Look, I was never under the illusion it would be easy. I knew my family was never going to be accepted as truly English. At first I tried to follow my mother-in-law, who was a stickler for tradition, but everything I did only made me stand out. Then I realized, I’ll never not stand out, so why fight it? I knew then I had to create my own style and do things my way.”

en: The first thing she did was give Greshamsbury Hall a sorely needed restoration—its first in more than a century. Out went the ancient Aga and the decomposing Tassinari et Chatel damask, and in came a bold, futurist East meets West look that designers now dub “Arabella Chic.” “I was the first to do forty-eight layers of tobacco lacquer on the floors of a manor house. I was the first to mix brutalist furniture with wicker.”
Sesotho: Ntho ea pele eo a e entseng e ne e fa Greshamsbury Hall haholo ho tsosolosoa ha eona pele ka lilemo tse fetang lekholo. Tsoa o ile a ea khale Aga le decomposing Tassinari et Chatel damask, 'me ka ba sebete, futurist East kopana le Bophirimela sheba Bophirima hore baqapi hona joale dub "Arabella Chic." "Ke ne ke le oa pele oa ho etsa likarolo tse mashome a mane a metso e robeli tsa lacquer ea koae mokatong oa ntlo ea manor. Ke ne ke le oa pele oa ho kopanya thepa ea sehlōhō le wicker. "
Yorùbá: Ohun àkọ́kọ́ tí ó ṣe ni láti fún Greshamsbury Hall ní ìmúpadàbọ̀ tí ó nílò gidi gan-an - àkọ́kọ́ rẹ̀ láti ju ọgọ́rùn-ún ọdún kan lọ. Aga àtijọ́ jáde lọ àti Tassinari et Chatel damask tí ó ti bàjẹ́, àti pé ìlà-oòrùn tí ó ní ìgboyà, ọjọ́ iwájú pàdé ìwò Ìwọ̀ Oòrùn tí àwọn aṣàpẹẹrẹ ń pè ní "Arabella Chic." "Mo jẹ akọkọ lati ṣe awọn fẹlẹfẹlẹ 48 ti lacquer taba lile lori awọn ilẹ ti ile manor kan. Èmi ni ẹni àkọ́kọ́ tí mo kọ́kọ́ ṣe àpòpọ̀ àwọn ohun ọ̀ṣọ́ oníwà ìkà pẹ̀lú wicker."
Setswana (Tswana): E ne ya re ka nako e e fetang lekgolo la dingwaga, o ne a dira tiro ya gagwe e e neng e le mo go yone e e neng e sa tlhole e le dingwaga di le 100. Out went ancient Aga and the decomposing Tassinari et Chatel damask, mme fa a ne a le pelokgale, futurist East ba kopana le Bophirima ba leba bophirima gore gompieno batlhami ba dub "Arabella Chic." "Ke ne ke le wa ntlha wa go dira di le 48 tsa go goga motsoko mo godimo ga ntlo ya manala a manala. Ke ne ke le motho wa ntlha go tlhakanya le didirisiwa tse di setlhogo."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): Te ohipa matamua ta'na i rave o te horo'araa ïa ia Greshamsbury Hall te hoê faaapîraa hinaaro-mau-hia—te matamua i roto hau atu i te hoê tenetere. I rapae au i te oire tahito no Aga e te mata'i rorofa'i Tassinari et Chatel damask, e i muri iho, ua tere mai te hoê mata'i rorofa'i i te pae Hitiaa o te râ ma, i te pae Too'a o te râ o te fenua Marite, e i teie nei, te parau nei te mau taata papa'i hoho'a e, "Arabella Chic ". " O vau te taata matamua tei rave i te ohipa puhipuhi avaava e maha ahuru ma va'u tuhaa i ni'a i te tahua o te hoê fare rahi. O vau te taata matamua tei ano'i i te mau tauihaa no te oro'a i ni'a i te tahua ha'utiraa ".
Maithili: पहिल काज जे ओ कयलनि ओ छल ग्रेशम्सबरी हॉलकेँ बहुत आवश्यक बहाली देनाइ - एक शताब्दीसँ बेसी समयमे ई पहिल बेर छल। प्राचीन आगा आ विघटित तसिनारी एट चेटेल दमास्कसँ बाहर निकलल, आ एकटा साहसिक, भविष्यवादी ईस्ट मीट्स वेस्ट लुक आयल जकरा डिजाइनर आब "अरबेला ठाठ" कहैत छथि। "हम सबसँ पहिने एकटा मनोर घरक फर्श पर तम्बाकू लाहक अड़तालीस परत केलहुँ। हम सबसँ पहिने ब्रूटालिस्ट फर्नीचर के विकर के संग मिला लेलहुं।
Malagasy: Ny zavatra voalohany nataony dia ny fanomezana ny Efitrano Greshamsbury ny famerenana amin'ny laoniny tena ilaina—voalohany tao anatin'ny zato taona mahery. en: Before her was an emerald-green lawn that sloped down to swaying palm trees and a blinding blue ocean. She padded barefoot across the grass down to the narrow strip of silver-gray sand where the waves lapped gently into shallow tide pools formed by lava rocks. It was her first time seeing the Pacific, and she scampered joyously over the rocks, looking for the perfect place to dip her feet into the crystalline waters.

en: “Not only that, but I think she saw what was special about the cabin, even though this isn’t her aesthetic. It’s no coincidence she put twelve surf cabins on the hills above her resort. Of course, hers are built of trendy blackened wood and are tricked out with cashmere throw pillows, soaking tubs, and movie screens that retract from the ceiling. She knows her crowd and she’s got the perfect plan to lure them here.”
Sesotho: Eseng hoo feela, empa ke ne ke nahana hore o ne a tseba hore na ke eng e khethehileng ka kamoreng ea hae, le hoja e ne e se botle ba hae. Ha ho makatse hore ebe o ile a beha likamore tse leshome le metso e 'meli tsa surf holim'a sebaka sa hae sa phomolo. Ehlile, mehlape e hahiloe ka lehong le letšo le letšo 'me le qhekelloa ka li-pillows tsa cashmere, ho inela li-tub, le li-skrini tsa lifilimi tse hulang siling. O tseba bongata ba hae, mme o na le leano le phethahetseng la ho ba hohela mona."
Yorùbá: "Kì í ṣe ìyẹn nìkan, ṣùgbọ́n mo rò pé ó rí ohun tí ó ṣe pàtàkì nípa àgọ́ náà, bí ó tilẹ̀ jẹ́ pé èyí kì í ṣe ẹwà rẹ̀. Kì í ṣe ìṣẹ̀lẹ̀ pé ó fi àwọn ilé ìgbafẹ́ méjìlá sí orí òkè lórí ibi ìgbafẹ́ rẹ̀. Lóòótọ́, wọ́n kọ́ tirẹ̀ pẹ̀lú igi dúdú ìgbàlódé tí wọ́n sì tàn wọ́n jẹ pẹ̀lú ìrọ̀rí cashmere throw, àwọn ìwẹ̀ ìwẹ̀, àti àwọn ìbòjú fíìmù tí ó yọ kúrò lórí àjà. en: The car turned off Kawaihae Road onto a narrow road that led to a newish-looking visitor’s center. “Take your time, and don’t go into the water in the bay unless you want to be shark food,” the driver quipped.
en_results: "title": "Hawaii: A Guide to the Islands","author": "David W. Forbes"
Sesotho: Koloi e ile ea tima Kawaihae Road ka tsela e moqotetsane e lebisitseng setsing sa baeti se shebahalang se secha. "Nka nako ea hao, 'me u se ke ua kena ka metsing ka bay ntle le haeba u batla ho ba lijo tsa shark," mokhanni o ile a tsamaea.
Yorùbá: Ọkọ̀ ayọ́kẹ́lẹ́ náà pa ọ̀nà Kawaihae sí ọ̀nà tó tóbi tí ó yọrí sí àárín àlejò tuntun. Awakọ̀ náà sọ pé, "Gba àkókò rẹ, má sì lọ sínú omi nínú òkun àyàfi tí o bá fẹ́ jẹ́ oúnjẹ ẹja ṣáàkì.
Setswana (Tswana): Koloi e ne ya tima Tsela ya Kawaihae mo tseleng e e pitlaganeng e e neng ya dira gore go nne le lefelo la baeng ba ba neng ba le gaufi. "Tsaya nako ya gago, o se ka wa tsena mo metsing kwa lewatleng ntle le fa o batla go nna dijo tsa shark."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): Ua û atu te pereoo i ni'a i te purumu no Kawaihae na ni'a i te hoê purumu pirihao e tae atu ai i te hoê pû fariiraa ratere apî. " A rave i to oe taime, e eiaha e haere i roto i te pape i roto i te ooa maori râ ia hinaaro oe i te amu i te maa ", te parau ïa a te taata faahoro.
Maithili: कार कवाइहे रोडकेँ एकटा संकीर्ण सड़क पर बंद कऽ देलक जाहिसँ एकटा नव दिखयवला आगंतुक केन्द्र दिस बढ़ि गेल। "अपन समय लिय, आ खाड़ीक पानिमे नहि जाउ जाधरि अहाँ शार्कक भोजन नहि बनय चाहैत छी," ड्राइवर चुटकी लेलक।
Malagasy: Niala tao amin'ny Lalana Kawaihae ilay fiara ka nandeha tamin'ny lalana tery izay nitondra nankany amin'ny foiben'ny mpitsidika iray vaovao. "Makà fotoana, ary aza miditra ao anaty rano ao amin'ny helodrano raha tsy hoe te-ho sakafo antsantsa ianao," hoy ilay mpamily namazivazy.

en: * The Big Island of Hawaii is the only island on Earth to possess ten of the world’s fourteen climate zones. This means you can sunbathe in the morning on a sizzling-hot beach in Kona, head to the Waimea Valley for a fog-bound lunch reminiscent of the Scottish Highlands, go hiking through the humid Puna rain forest in an afternoon downpour, and freeze your ass off on the summit of Mauna Kea at sunset.
en_results: "title": "Hawaii: A Traveler's Guide to the Big Island","author": "Jennifer Blanton"
Sesotho: Sehlekehleke se Seholo sa Hawaii ke sehlekehleke se le seng feela lefatšeng se nang le libaka tse leshome le metso e mene tsa maemo a leholimo. Sena se bolela hore u ka sunbathe hoseng ka sizzling-chesang lebōpong ka Kona, hlooho ho waimea Valley bakeng sa lijo tsa motšehare moholi-tlama hopotsang Scottish Highlands, tsamaea hloa ka mongobo Puna pula morung ka shoalane ka shoalane, 'me u bata ass hao theoha tlhōrōng ea Mauna Kea ha letsatsi le likela.
Yorùbá: * Erékùṣù ńlá Hawaii nìkan ni erékùṣù tó wà lórí ilẹ̀ ayé tí ó ní mẹ́wàá nínú àwọn agbègbè ojú ọjọ́ mẹ́rìnlá àgbáyé. Èyí túmọ̀ sí pé o lè gbá oòrùn ní òwúrọ̀ ní etí òkun gbígbóná ní Kona, lọ sí Àfonífojì Waimea fún oúnjẹ ọ̀sán tí ó so mọ́ ìkùukùu tí ó ń rántí highlands Scotland, lọ rin ìrìn-àjò nípasẹ̀ igbó òjò Puna tó tutù nínú òjò ọ̀sán, kí o sì dí ìdí rẹ lórí òkè Mauna Kea nígbà tí oòrùn bá wọ̀.
Setswana (Tswana): Setlhaketlhake se se golo sa Hawaii ke sone fela se se nang le ditshika tse di lesome tsa maemo a loapi mo lefatsheng. Se se raya gore o ka sunbathe mo mosong mo lotshitshing lo lo mogote kwa Kona, kwa Nokeng ya Waimea go ya go ja dijo tsa motshegare tse di gopolelang kwa dithabeng tsa Scotland, o ya go tsamaya mo sekgweng se se nang le pula ya Puna e e mogote mo tlase ga bosigo, mme o tsidifale motlhaba wa gago mo setlhoeng sa Mauna Kea fa letsatsi le phirima.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): * O te motu Big Island no Vaihi ana'e te motu i nia i te Fenua o te fana'o hoê ahuru tuhaa o te ahuara'i o te ao nei. To'na auraa ra, e nehenehe ïa ta outou e haere i te po'ipo'i na ni'a i te hoê tahatai ve'ave'a i Kona, te upoo e tae atu ai i te afaa no Waimea no te hoê tamaaraa i te avatea, e haere e orihaere na roto i te uru raau haumi no Puna i te avatea, e e tatara i to outou mau asini i ni'a i te tupuai mou'a no Mauna Kea i te toparaa mahana.
Maithili: * हवाईक बिग आइलैंड पृथ्वीक एकमात्र द्वीप अछि जतय दुनियाक चौदह जलवायु क्षेत्रमेसँ दस टा अछि। एकर अर्थ अछि जे अहाँ भोरमे कोनाक एकटा सिजलिंग-गर्म समुद्र तट पर धूप मे स्नान कऽ सकैत छी, स्कॉटिश हाइलैंड्सक स्मरण करयवला कुहेसक लेल वैमिया घाटी जा सकैत छी, दुपहरक बरखामे आर्द्र पुना वर्षा वनसँ पैदल यात्रा कऽ सकैत छी, आ सूर्यास्तक समय मौना कीक शिखर पर अपन गधाकेँ जम सकैत छी।
Malagasy: Ny Nosy Lehibe Hawaii no hany nosy eto an - tany manana ny folo amin'ireo faritra efatra ambin'ny folo momba ny toetrandro. en: Father and daughter proceeded up the steps of the ice palace and came upon a banquet hall with three immensely long tables carved entirely out of ice, the frozen blocks filled with flowers and hauntingly lit so that the petals seemed suspended in space. Above the tables hovered six enormous crystal chandeliers lit with hundreds of candles, and the open archways at the far end of the palace perfectly framed the stupendous views. The sun had just dipped below the clouds, rendering the sky a deep violet that shimmered through the crystalline walls of the palace.
Sesotho: Ntate le morali ba ile ba ea mehatong ea ntlo ea borena ea leqhoa 'me ba tla ka kamoreng ea mokete e nang le litafole tse tharo tse telele tse betliloeng ka ho feletseng ka leqhoa, li-block tse hoammeng li tletse lipalesa' me li chesehela hoo liphoofolo tse ruuoang lapeng li neng li bonahala li emisitsoe sebakeng. Ka holim'a litafole hovered li-chandeliers tse tšeletseng tse kholo tsa kristale tse nang le likerese tse makholo, le li-archways tse bulehileng qetellong e hole ea ntlo ea borena ka mokhoa o phethahetseng li ne li etsa lipono tse makatsang. Letsatsi le ne le sa tsoa kolobisitsoe ka tlase ho maru, le fana ka leholimo e le violet e tebileng e neng e shimmered ka mabota a kristale ea ntlo ea borena.
Yorùbá: Bàbá àti ọmọbìnrin tẹ̀síwájú ní àwọn ìgbésẹ̀ ààfin yìnyín ó sì wá sí gbọ̀ngàn àsè pẹ̀lú tábìlì gígùn mẹ́ta tí wọ́n gbẹ́ pátápátá láti inú yìnyín, àwọn ilé dídì tí ó kún fún òdòdó tí wọ́n sì tan iná kí àwọn òdòdó náà lè dà bí ẹni pé wọ́n dá àwọn òdòdó dúró nínú òfuurufú. Lókè àwọn tábìlì náà gbé àwọn iná kirisita ńlá mẹ́fà tí wọ́n tan iná pẹ̀lú ọgọ́rọ̀ọ̀rún àbẹ́là, àti pé àwọn ọ̀nà ìṣísílẹ̀ ní òpin ààfin náà ṣe àgbékalẹ̀ àwọn ìwòye tí kò dára. Oòrùn ṣẹ̀ṣẹ̀ rì sí abẹ́ àwọsánmọ̀, tí ó sọ ọ̀run di violet tó jinlẹ̀ tí ó tàn láti inú ògiri ààfin crystalline.
Setswana (Tswana): Rre le morwadi ba ne ba tsena mo matlong a ntlo ya segosi mme ba tsena mo ntlong ya go ja dijo tse tharo tse di telele tse di betlilweng go tswa mo godimo ga ice, dithupa tse di tsididi di tletse dithunya le go kgabisa mo go neng go bonala di emisitse mo lefelong. Mo godimo ga ditafole di ne tsa phatsima di le thataro tse dikgolo tsa kristale tse di neng di na le dikandelare di le makgolokgolo, mme meraka e e bulegileng kwa bofelong jwa ntlo ya segosi e e kwa bofelong jwa ntlo ya borena e ne ya dira gore go nne le dipono tse di gakgamatsang. Letsatsi le ne le sa tswa go tsena mo marung, le ne le dira loapi lo lo tseneletseng lo lo neng lo kgaratlha ka mabota a a kwa godimo a ntlo ya borena.

en: “I meant every word of it. And after you spent the night in Puako, after that shower under the moonlight, I haven’t been able to stop thinking about you. I can still smell you on my sheets, and seeing you tonight, looking so unbelievably beautiful, I just needed to—”
Sesotho: "Ke bolela lentsoe le leng le le leng la sena. 'Me ka mor'a hore u qete bosiu Puako, ka mor'a hore u shaoara tlas'a khoeli ea khoeli, ha kea ka ka khaotsa ho nahana ka uena. Ke ntse ke ka u fofonela mahlong a ka, 'me ke u bona kajeno, ke shebahala ke le motle haholo, ke ne ke hloka feela ho e sebelisa hape. "
Yorùbá: "Mo tumọ si gbogbo ọrọ rẹ. Lẹ́yìn ìgbà tí o lo alẹ́ náà ní Puako, lẹ́yìn ìwẹ̀ yẹn lábẹ́ ìmọ́lẹ̀ òṣùpá, mi ò tí ì lè dáwọ́ ìrònú dúró nípa rẹ. Mo ṣì lè gbóòórùn rẹ lórí aṣọ ìbùsùn mi, kí n sì rí ọ lálẹ́ yìí, mo rẹwà gan-an, mo kàn nílò láti-"
Setswana (Tswana): 'I meant every word of this' - Ke tlhotlheleditswe ke mafoko otlhe a Mme fa o sena go fetsa bosigo kwa Puako, morago ga go tlhapa ka fa tlase ga ngwedi, ga ke ise ke kgone go tlogela go akanya ka wena. Ke kgona go go bona o le moseding bosigong jo bo fetileng, ke sa ntse ke go bona o le montle thata, ke ne ke sa batle go dira jalo.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Ua parau vau i te mau parau atoa o te reira. E i muri a'e i to oe faaearaa i Puako i te po, i muri a'e i taua hopuraa pape ra i raro a'e i te ava'e, aita vau i nehenehe e faaea i te mana'ona'o ia oe. E nehenehe noa â ta'u e hau'a ia oe i ni'a i ta'u mau tapo'i ro'i, e ia hi'o vau ia oe i teie pô, ma te hi'o ti'a'tu i ni'a, e mea nehenehe mau, o ta'u i hinaaro noa na—"
Maithili: "हम एकर हर शब्द के मतलब छलहुं। आ अहां के पुआको मे राति बितेलाक बाद, चाँदनी के नीचा ओहि बौछार के बाद, हम अहां के बारे मे सोचनाइ बंद नहि कए सकलहुं। हम एखनो अपन चादर पर अहां के सूंघ सकैत छी, आ आइ राति अहां के देखैत छी, एतेक अविश्वसनीय रूप सँ सुंदर देखैत छी, हमरा बस एकर जरूरत छल-"
Malagasy: "Ny teny rehetra no tiako holazaina. Ary taorian'ny nandanianao ny alina tao Puako, taorian'ny fandroana tao ambanin'ny hazavan'ny volana, tsy afaka nitsahatra nieritreritra momba anao aho. Mbola afaka manimbolo anao eo amin'ny lambako aho, ary mahita anao anio alina, toy ny tsara tarehy tsy mampino, mila manao izany fotsiny aho—"
Divehi (Dhivehi): އޭގެ ކޮންމެ ބަހެއް ވެސް އަހަރެން މާނަކުރީމެވެ. އަދި ބައްޕަ ޕުއާކޯގައި ރޭގަނޑު ހޭދަކުރުމަށްފަހު، ހަނދުވަރުގެ ދަށުގައި އެ ފެންވަރާލުމަށްފަހު، ބައްޕައާ މެދު ވިސްނުން ހުއްޓައެއް ނުލެވުނެވެ. އަދިވެސް އަހަރެންގެ ޝީޓުތަކުގައި ކަލޭގެ ވަސް ދުވޭ، އަދި މިރޭ ބައްޕަ ފެނުމުން، އެހާ ގަބޫލު ނުކުރެވޭ ވަރުގެ ރީތި، އައި ޖަސްޓް ނީޑް ޓު...".

en: “I feel we should use a portion of Henry’s windfall to help the Gaos obtain the best solicitor possible. Perhaps they can help get him a reduced sentence. It does no one any good for this boy to rot away in prison during the most productive years of his life.”
Sesotho: "Ke nahana hore re lokela ho sebelisa karolo e 'ngoe ea li-windfall tsa Henry ho thusa Gaos ho fumana solicitor e ntle ka ho fetisisa. Mohlomong ba ka mo thusa hore a be le kahlolo e fokolang. Ho ke ke ha e-ba le e 'ngoe e ntle hore ngoana enoa a bolaee chankaneng nakong ea lilemo tse behang ka ho fetisisa tsa bophelo ba hae. "
Yorùbá: "Mo ro pe o yẹ ki a lo apakan kan ti afẹfẹ Henry lati ṣe iranlọwọ fun Gaos lati gba agbẹjọro ti o dara julọ ti o ṣeeṣe. Bóyá wọ́n lè ràn án lọ́wọ́ láti fún un ní ìdínkù gbólóhùn. Kò ṣe ẹni tí ó dára fún ọmọkùnrin yìí láti bàjẹ́ nínú ẹ̀wọ̀n ní àwọn ọdún tí ó dára jùlọ nínú ayé rẹ̀."
Setswana (Tswana): "Ke ne ke akanya gore re tshwanetse go dirisa sedirisiwa sa ga Jehofa go thusa batho ba ba nang le bokgoni jo bo botoka. Gongwe ba ka mo thusa go dira gore a se ka a nna le bothata jo bo kwa tlase. Ga go na ope yo o ka dirang gore ngwana yono a bolae mo kgolegelong mo dingwageng tse di molemo thata tsa botshelo jwa gagwe."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Te mana'o nei au e, e ti'a ia taua ia faaohipa i te hoê tuhaa o te mata'i rorofa'i a Henry no te tauturu i te mau Gaos ia farii i te rave'a maitai roa a'e. Peneia'e e nehenehe ratou e tauturu ia ' na ia faaiti mai i ta ' na utua. Aita e maitai no teie tamaiti ia haere ê atu i roto i te fare tape'araa i te mau matahiti hotu roa a'e o to'na oraraa ".
Maithili: "हमरा लगैत अछि जे हमरासभकेँ हेनरीक अप्रत्याशित प्रदर्शनक एकटा हिस्साक उपयोग गाओसकेँ सर्वोत्तम सॉलिसिटर प्राप्त करबामे सहायता करबाक चाही। संभवतः ओ हुनका कम सजा देबामे सहायता कऽ सकैत छथि। एहि लड़काक जीवनक सबसँ उत्पादक वर्षमे जेलमे सड़ि जेनाइ केकरो नीक नहि अछि।"
Malagasy: "Tsapanay fa tokony hampiasa ampahany amin'ny fitsokan'i Henry isika mba hanampiana ireo Gaos hahazo ny mpisolovava tsara indrindra. Angamba afaka manampy azy hampihena ny sazy izy ireo. Tsy misy olona tsara ho an'ity zazalahy ity ny migadra mandritra ireo taona mamokatra indrindra teo amin'ny fiainany.
Divehi (Dhivehi): "އަޅުގަނޑަށް ހީވަނީ ހެންރީގެ ވިންޑްފޯލްގެ ބައެއް ބޭނުންކޮށްގެން ގާއޯސް އަށް އެންމެ ރަނގަޅު ސޮލިސިޓާ ހޯދުމުގައި އެހީތެރިވެދޭން ޖެހޭ ކަމަށް. އެމީހުންނަށް އޭނާއަށް ކުޑަ އަދަބެއް ހޯދައިދިނުމަށް އެހީތެރިވެދެވިދާނެއެވެ. ހަޔާތުގެ އެންމެ އުފެއްދުންތެރި އަހަރުތަކުގައި މި ކުއްޖާ ޖަލުގައި ރޮއިގަތުމަކީ އެއްވެސް މީހަކަށް ކުރާނެ ކަމެއް ނޫނެވެ.

en: “Pointless—the lava just obliterates everything in its path. Only a matter of days till the entire resort is destroyed. Thank god no houses or towns are in danger. The Hawaii County Civil Defense Agency wants to declare all of Bellaloha a disaster zone.”
Sesotho: 18:18)) Ka hona, o ne a sa tsebe hore na ke eng eo u ka e bonang e le ntho e 'ngoe le e' ngoe eo ue hlokang kelellong, e leng ntho e 'ngoe le e' ngoe Ke taba ea matsatsi feela ho fihlela sebaka sohle se fela. Kea leboha Molimo, ha ho na matlo kapa metse e kotsing. Mokhatlo oa Ts'ireletso ea Sechaba oa Hawaii o batla ho phatlalatsa tsohle tsa Bellaloha sebaka sa likoluoa. "
Yorùbá: "Láìsí ìtumọ̀ - lava ṣẹ̀ṣẹ̀ pa gbogbo nkan run ní ọ̀nà rẹ̀. Ọjọ́ díẹ̀ péré ni títí tí gbogbo ibi ìsinmi náà yóò fi parun. Ọlọ́run dúpẹ́ pé kò sí ilé tàbí ìlú tí ó wà nínú ewu. Ilé-iṣẹ́ ìdáàbòbò ìlú Hawaii County fẹ́ kéde gbogbo Bellaloha gẹ́gẹ́ bí agbègbè àjálù."
Setswana (Tswana): 'O ne a ôtlhama fêla mo tseleng ya gagwê' - The pond just obliterates all in its way Ke fela malatsi a le mmalwa fela go fitlha tiro yotlhe e senngwa. Lebogang Modimo ga a na magae le metse e e mo kotsing. 'Ba ne ba ôtlhamêlô ya go ôna mo motseng mongwe le mongwe' - The village of the villages wants to declare all of the villages
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " E mea papû e, e nehenehe ta te vari paruparu e faaino i te mau mea atoa i ni'a i to'na e'a. Tau mahana noa e tae roa ' tu i te taime e haamouhia ' i te vahi raveraa ohipa taatoa. Mauruuru i te mea e, aita e fare e aore râ, e oire tei roto i te ati. Te hinaaro nei te Pû Parururaa Tivira no Hawaii ia faariro i te taato'araa o Bellaloha ei tuhaa fenua ati ".
Maithili: "व्यर्थ—लावा बस अपन रास्तामे सब किछु मिटा दैत अछि। पूरा रिसॉर्ट नष्ट होयबा धरि मात्र किछु दिनक बात। भगवानक शुक्र अछि जे कोनो घर या कस्बा खतरामे नहि अछि। हवाई काउंटी सिविल डिफेंस एजेंसी पूरा बेल्लालोहाकेँ आपदा क्षेत्र घोषित करय चाहैत अछि।
Malagasy: "Tsy misy dikany—mamafa ny zava-drehetra amin'ny làlany fotsiny ny lava. Andro vitsivitsy sisa dia ho rava tanteraka ny toeram-pialan-tsasatra. Misaotra an'Andriamanitra fa tsy misy trano na tanàna tandindomin-doza. Ny Masoivoho Fiarovana Sivily ao amin'ny Fivondronan'i Hawaii dia maniry ny hanambara ny Bellaloha ho faritra misy loza.
Divehi (Dhivehi): "ބޭކާރު- ލާވާގެ ސަބަބުން އޭގެ މަގުގައިވާ ހުރިހާ އެއްޗެއް ނައްތާލެވިއްޖެ. މުޅި ރިސޯޓް ހަލާކުވާން ދެން އޮތީ މަދު ދުވަސްކޮޅެކެވެ. މާތް الله އަށް ޝުކުރުވެރިވާށެވެ! އެއްވެސް ގެއަކަށް ނުވަތަ އަވަށަކަށް ނުރައްކަލެއް ނެތެވެ. ހަވާއީ ކައުންޓީ ސިވިލް ޑިފެންސް އޭޖެންސީން ބޭނުންވަނީ މުޅި ބެލާލޯހާ އަކީ ޑިޒާސްޓާ ޒޯނެއްގެ ގޮތުގައި ކަނޑައެޅުމަށެވެ."

en: “Even if we sold off all the hotels, there’s still a huge shortfall because of Bellaloha. We’d still be about two fifty to three hundred million in the hole.”
Sesotho: "Le ha re rekisa lihotele tsohle, ho ntse ho na le bothata bo boholo ka lebaka la Bellaloha. Re ne re ka ba limilione tse peli ho isa ho tse makholo a mararo ka sekoting. "
Yorùbá: "Kódà bí a bá ta gbogbo àwọn ilé ìtura náà tán, àìsí ńlá ṣì wà nítorí Bellaloha. A ṣì máa tó mílíọ̀nù méjì sí mẹ́ta nínú ihò náà."
Setswana (Tswana): "Le fa re ne re rekisa dihotele tsotlhe, go sa ntse go na le tlhaelo e kgolo ka ntlha ya ga Bellaloha. 'Re tlaa bo re le dimilione di le 25 go ya go di le 300 000 mo lebaleng la rona' - We will be 25 to 3 million in the hole
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Noa'tu e, e hoo matou i te mau hotera atoa, te vai noa ra â te hoê toparaa pape rahi no Bellaloha. E piti ahuru e tae atu i te toru hanere milioni matou i roto i te apoo ".
Maithili: "भले हम सभ होटल बेचि देलौं मुदा बेल्लालोहाक कारण एखनो भारी कमी अछि। हम एखनो छेद मे लगभग दू पचास सँ तीन सौ करोड़ रहब।
Malagasy: "Na dia nivarotra ny trano fandraisam-bahiny rehetra aza izahay, mbola misy ny tsy fahampiana goavana noho ny Bellaloha. Mbola eo amin'ny 50 ka hatramin'ny 300 tapitrisa eo ho eo izahay ao anatin'ilay lavaka."
Divehi (Dhivehi): "ހުރިހާ ހޮޓަލެއް ވިއްކާލި ކަމުގައި ވިޔަސް ބެލާލޯހާގެ ސަބަބުން އަދިވެސް ވަރަށް ބޮޑު އުނިކަމެއް އެބަހުރި. އަދިވެސް އެ ހޮޅީގައި ގާތްގަނޑަކަށް ދެ ފަންސާސް ތިންސަތޭކަ މިލިއަނާ ދެމެދުގެ އަދަދަކަށް ހުންނާނެ."

en: *2 In reality, it would be difficult for a lion to kill a grown ostrich. Lions are terrific sprinters with a top speed of over eighty kmh, but they can only maintain this speed for very short periods. Ostriches may only manage seventy kmh, but they have much greater stamina and could outrun a lazy lion. BUT…lions are skilled predators and could ambush the ostrich in a sneak attack. However, the ostrich has two extremely sharp claws on each foot, allowing it to, hypothetically, disembowel a lion with a single well-placed kick. All this is rather moot, because lions don’t particularly enjoy the taste of ostrich. They much prefer antelope or zebra, served very rare.
Sesotho: 2 Ha e le hantle, ho ka ba thata hore tau e bolaee e hōlileng. Litau ke sprinters e makatsang e nang le lebelo le phahameng la lik'hilomithara tse fetang 80, empa li ka boloka lebelo lena feela ka linako tse khuts'oane haholo. Li-ostries li ka laola lik'hilomithara tse mashome a supileng feela, empa li na le li-stamina tse kholo haholo 'me li ka tsoa tau e botsoa. EMPA ... Litau ke li-predator tse nang le tsebo 'me li ka lalla ostrich tlhaselong ea sneak. Leha ho le joalo, ostrich e na le li-claws tse peli tse bohale haholo leotong le leng le le leng, ho e lumella, ka hypothetically, e leng tau e nang le kick e le 'ngoe e behiloeng hantle. Sena sohle ke moot, hobane litau ha li natefeloe haholo ke tatso ea ostrich. Li rata li-antelope kapa li-zebra, li sebeletsa ka seoelo haholo.
Yorùbá: *2 Ni otitọ, yoo nira fun kiniun lati pa ostrich ti o dagba. en: RG: Thank god for that. Isn’t it strange…when the lava is done doing its thing, it will be like Mum’s resort was never there. It’s sort of poetic in a way.

en: “Yes. But what gets me is her clenched fist and that look of rage in her face,” the docent remarked. “Marvelous, isn’t it? She clearly can’t fathom how she went from a rich woman to ending up in such a squalid, pathetic state.”
Sesotho: "Ho joalo. "Empa ke eng e etsang hore ke se ke ka e etsa hore ke be le maikutlo a hae a ho halefa le ho hlonama sefahlehong sa hae," ha rialo Motlatsi. "Hoa makatsa, na ha ho joalo? O ne a sa khone ho hlalosa kamoo a ileng a tsoa ho mosali ea ruileng kateng ho felisa boemong bo joalo ba ho sotha, pathetic. "
Yorùbá: Aa Ṣùgbọ́n ohun tí ó mú mi ni ọwọ́ rẹ̀ tí ó di ọwọ́ rẹ̀ mú àti ìrísí ìbínú yẹn ní ojú rẹ̀," ìgòkè náà sọ. Ó ìåíÿ åñòü, à? Ó hàn gbangba pé kò lè mọ bí ó ṣe lọ láti ọ̀dọ̀ obìnrin ọlọ́rọ̀ kan sí ìparí ní irú ipò ìbànújẹ́ bẹ́ẹ̀."
Setswana (Tswana): Mme E. E. "Ke eng se se dirang gore ke nne le pelo ya me e e nkgang e bile ke ikutlwa ke le bogale mo sefatlhegong sa gagwe," ga bua Jalo. "Go a gakgamatsa, a ga go jalo? Ga a ka ke a kgona go lemoga gore o ne a tswa mo mosading yo o humileng yo o neng a le mo seemong se se ntseng jalo sa go nna le maemo a a kwa godimo."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " E. Tera râ, te mea e haaputapû nei ia'u, o to'na ïa hoho'a mata riri e te riri i roto i to'na hoho'a mata ", te parau ïa a te vahine hoo. " E mea maere, e ere anei ? E mea papû maitai e, aita oia e taa ra e, e mea nahea to'na faaru'eraa i te hoê vahine tao'a rahi no te tapae i roto i te hoê huru oraraa veve e te oto ".
Maithili: "हँ। मुदा जे हमरा भेटैत अछि ओ अछि ओकर मुट्ठी आ ओकर चेहरा पर क्रोधक रूप," डोसेंट टिप्पणी कयलनि। "अद्भुत, नहि? ओ स्पष्ट रूपसँ थाह नहि पाबि सकैत छथि जे ओ कोना एकटा धनी महिलासँ एतेक अशिष्ट, दयनीय स्थितिमे समाप्त भऽ गेलीह।"
Malagasy: "Eny. Saingy ny tena mahatonga ahy dia ny totohondriny sy ny endrika hatezerana eo amin'ny tarehiny," hoy ny fanamarihan'ilay docent. "Mahagaga izany, sa tsy izany? Mazava ho azy fa tsy azony an-tsaina ny fomba nialany tamin'ny vehivavy manan-karena ka niafara tamin'ny toe-javatra mampalahelo sy mampalahelo tahaka izao."
Divehi (Dhivehi): "އާނ. އެކަމަކު އަޅުގަނޑަށް ލިބޭ އެއްޗަކީ އޭނާގެ މުށިގަނޑާއި އެ މޫނުމަތިން ފެންނަމުން ދިޔަ ރުޅިވެރިކަމުގެ އެ ސިފަ،" ޑޯސެންޓް ބުންޏެވެ. en: The massive chiseled-and-hammered-copper double doors on the east side of the courtyard opened slowly as four men cloaked in hooded white and gold djellabas astride four white horses were silhouetted in the doorway. The horses cantered into the courtyard and came to a standstill by the central fountain, and the riders jumped off their horses and flung off their hoods, revealing themselves to be the two groomsmen, the best man, and the groom. The assembled guests applauded at the audacious entrance.
Sesotho: Monyako o moholo oa chiseled-and-hammered-koporo habeli ka lehlakoreng le ka bochabela la lebala la buloa butle joalo ka banna ba bane ba apereng hooded tšoeu le khauta djellabas astride lipere tse 'nè tse tšoeu li ne li silhouetted monyako. 13Yaba ba dula le yena, ba tla le bona, ba neng ba le hara bona, ba neng ba le hara bona, ba tla ba le melala e mmedi, ba tla ba le melala e metle ka ho fetisisa, ba tla e amohela matsohong a bona. Baithaopi ba ile ba amohela baeti ba neng ba le haufi le monyako.
Yorùbá: Àwọn ilẹ̀kùn méjì ńlá tí wọ́n gbẹ́ tí wọ́n sì ṣe bàbà ní apá ìlà-oòrùn àgbàlá ṣí sílẹ̀ díẹ̀díẹ̀ bí àwọn ọkùnrin mẹ́rin tí wọ́n wọ aṣọ djellabas funfun àti wúrà ṣe ń lu ẹṣin funfun mẹ́rin ní ẹnu-ọ̀nà. Àwọn ẹṣin náà wọ inú àgbàlá wọ́n sì dúró lẹ́gbẹ̀ẹ́ orísun àárín gbùngbùn, àwọn ẹlẹ́ṣin sì fò kúrò nínú ẹṣin wọn wọ́n sì fọ́ àwọn ìbòjú wọn, tí wọ́n fi ara wọn hàn gẹ́gẹ́ bí ọkọ ìyàwó méjèèjì, ọkùnrin tí ó dára jùlọ, àti ọkọ ìyàwó. Àwọn àlejò tí wọ́n péjọ pàtẹ́wọ́ sí ẹnu ọ̀nà ìgboyà.
Setswana (Tswana): Diheketara tse pedi tsa koporo tse kgubedu tse kgubedu di ne di butswe ka iketlo jwalo ka banna ba bane ba neng ba apere diaparo tse tshweu tse tshweu le tsa kgauta tse tshweu tse tshweu di ne di le mane tse tshweu monyako. 13Bapalami ba dipere ba ne ba le ka lebaleng, mme ba tsamaya ba eme pela sediba se bohareng, mme bapalami ba tlolela dipere tsa bona, ba tlatlapa difaha, ba itlhaola, e le monyadiwa ba babedi, le monyadi. Baeng ba ba neng ba le mo lefelong le ba neng ba le mo go lona ba ne ba le mo tseleng e ba neng ba le mo go yona.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): Ua matara mărû noa te mau opani rahi i te pae hitiaa o te râ o te aua, i te mea e, e maha taata tei ahuhia i te ahu uouo e te auro, e maha puaahorofenua uouo i mua i te uputa. Ua tomo atura te mau puaahorofenua i roto i te aua e ua mau atura i te hiti o te apoo pape no ropu, e ua ou'a a'era te feia faahoro i nia i ta ratou mau puaahorofenua e ua taue atura i ta ratou mau puaahorofenua, ma te faaite mai e o raua na tane faaipoipo e piti, te tane maitai roa ' ' e, e te tane faaipoipo apî. Ua haapopou te mau manihini i ruru mai i te uputa tomoraa ino mau.
Maithili: आँगनक पूरब दिस विशाल छेनी आ हथौड़ासँ बनल ताम्बाक दोहरा दरवाजा धीरे-धीरे खुजल जखन चारि गोट आदमी हुड वला उज्जर आ सोनाक जेल्लाबा पहिरने छलाह जाहिमे चारिटा उज्जर घोड़ा छल, दुआरि पर सिल्हूट कयल गेल छल। घोड़ासभ आँगनमे घुसि गेल आ केन्द्रीय फव्वारा लग ठप भऽ गेल, आ सवारसभ अपन घोड़ासँ कूदि कऽ अपन हुड फेंकि देलक, जाहिसँ अपनाकेँ दूटा दूल्हा, सबसँ नीक आदमी, आ वर कहल गेल। जुटल अतिथि लोकनि दुस्साहसी प्रवेश द्वार पर ताली बजौलनि।
Malagasy: Nisokatra tsimoramora ireo varavarana roa goavana vita amin'ny kodiaran-droa teo amin'ny ilany atsinanan'ny tokotany raha nisy lehilahy efatra nitafy djellabas fotsy sy volamena nisaron-tava tamin'ny soavaly fotsy efatra teo amin'ny varavarana. Niditra tao an - tokotany ireo soavaly, ary nijanona teo akaikin'ny loharano afovoany. Nitsambikina avy teo amin'ny soavaliny ireo mpitaingina ary niendaka teo amin'ny saron - dohany, ka nilaza fa izy roa lahy no lehilahy tsara indrindra, ary ilay mpampakatra. Nitehaka teo amin'ny fidirana feno fahasahiana ireo vahiny nivory.
Divehi (Dhivehi): ހުދުކުލައިގެ ހުދު ކުލައާއި ރަން ކުލައިގެ ޑިޖެލަބާސް އަޅައިގެން ހުދު ކުލައިގެ ހަތަރު އަސްމަތީގައި ތިބި ހަތަރު ފިރިހެނުން ދޮރުމަތީގައި ސިލޫއޭޓް ކުރަމުން ދިޔައިރު، ގޯތިތެރޭގެ އިރުމަތީ ފަރާތުގައި ހުރި ބޮޑު ޗިސެލްޑް-އެންޑް-ހެމަރޑް-ކޮޕަރ ޑަބަލް ދޮރުތައް މަޑުމަޑުން ހުޅުވިގެން ދިޔައެވެ. އެ އަސްތައް ގޯތިތެރެއަށް ވަދެ، މެދު ފެންވަރާ ކައިރިއަށް އައިސް ހުއްޓުމަކަށް އައެވެ. އަދި ސަވާރުން އެމީހުންގެ އަސްތަކުން ފުންމާލައި، އެމީހުންގެ ހޫޑުތައް އެއްލާލީ، ދެ ގްރޫމްމެންނާއި، އެންމެ މޮޅު ފިރިހެން މީހާ އާއި، ދެމަފިރިންކަން ހާމަކުރަމުންނެވެ. އެއްވެ ތިބި މެހުމާނުން ހިތްވަރުގަދަ ދޮރުމަތީގައި ތައުރީފު ކުރިއެވެ.

en: “No, I fly mainly in Cappadocia. This is new terrain for me, but we’ve been rehearsing all week, and praying for the weather to cooperate. Today has been perfect, although I’m sure quite a few balloons will be blown off course. Thankfully, there’s a Jeep assigned to each balloon, following from below. So if we land in Agadir, so be it.”
Sesotho: Che, ke fofa haholo-holo Holong ea Cappadocia. Ena ke sebaka se secha ho nna, empa esale re ntse re ithuta beke kaofela, 'me re rapella boemo ba leholimo ho sebelisana. Kajeno e bile e phethahetseng, empa ke na le bonnete ba hore li-balloon tse 'maloa li tla fefoloa. Ka lehlohonolo, ho na le jeep e abetsoeng ballon e 'ngoe le e' ngoe, e latelang ho tloha ka tlase. 'Me haeba re lula naheng ea Habo, e ke e-ba joalo. "
Yorùbá: "Rárá, mo fò ní pàtàkì ní Cappadocia. Ilẹ̀ tuntun nìyí fún mi, ṣùgbọ́n a ti ń ṣe ìgbáradì ní gbogbo ọ̀sẹ̀, a sì ń gbàdúrà fún ojú ọjọ́ láti fọwọ́sowọ́pọ̀. Òní ti pé, bí ó tilẹ̀ jẹ́ pé ó dá mi lójú pé àwọn bọ́ọ̀lù díẹ̀ ni wọ́n máa fọ́ kúrò lójú ọ̀nà. A dúpẹ́, Jeep kan wà tí wọ́n yàn fún bọ́ọ̀lù kọ̀ọ̀kan, tí ó tẹ̀lé e láti ìsàlẹ̀. Nítorí náà tí a bá balẹ̀ ní Agadir, bẹ́ẹ̀ ni kí ó rí bẹ́ẹ̀."
Setswana (Tswana): "No, yo ya me lo y me lo y a le cappadocia." E ne e le tiro e e molemo, mme re ntse re rapela gore re nne le seabe mo bekeng e e fetileng, mme re ntse re rapela gore re kgone go dira dilo tse di molemo. Gompieno go ne go na le dilo tse dintsi tse di sa siamang, le fa ke itse gore go na le dilo di le mmalwa tse di sa siamang. Ke a leboga, go na le tšhono e nngwe le e nngwe e e neng e le mo go yone, e e fa tlase. Fa re le mo lefatsheng la ga Asare, re tla bo re le mo go lone."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Aita, te rere nei au na ni'a i te manureva i Cappadocia. E fenua apî teie no'u, tera râ, ua haere noa matou i te pureraa i te hepetoma taatoa, e ua pure matou ia maitai mai te mahana. I teie mahana, e mea maitai roa, noa'tu e, ua papû ia'u e, e topa te tahi mau ofa'i pupuhi i ni'a i te e'a. Auaa râ, te vai ra te hoê Jeep i faataahia no te mau tao'a tahi ora atoa, ma te apeehia mai i raro nei. No reira, mai te mea e, e tau tatou i Agadir, ia na reira atoa ïa tatou ".
Maithili: "नहि, हम मुख्य रूप सं कैप्पाडोसिया मे उड़ैत छी। ई हमरा लेल नव भूभाग अछि, मुदा हम सभ सप्ताह अभ्यास कऽ रहल छी, आ मौसमक सहयोगक लेल प्रार्थना करैत रहल छी। आइ एकदम सही रहल अछि, यद्यपि हमरा विश्वास अछि जे किछु गुब्बारा उड़ि जायत। शुक्र अछि जे नीच्चाँसँ प्रत्येक गुब्बाराकेँ एकटा जीप देल गेल अछि। तेँ जँ हम अगादिर मे उतरैत छी, तखन होइ।
Malagasy: "Tsia, ny fiaramanidina no tena tiako indrindra ao Cappadocia. Vaovao ho ahy izany, saingy nanao famerenana nandritra ny herinandro izahay, ary nivavaka mba hiarahan'ny toetr'andro. Androany dia tonga lafatra, na dia azoko antoka aza fa hisy balaonina vitsivitsy ho voaroaka amin'ny lalana. Soa ihany fa misy Jeep iray voatondro isaky ny balaonina, manaraka avy eto ambany. Ary [tsy nandeha] teny amin'ireo [mpangataka] izay mifindrafindra mitety fiara izahay.
Divehi (Dhivehi): "ނޫން، އަހަރެން މައިގަނޑު ގޮތެއްގައި އުދުހެނީ ކެޕަޑޯޝިއާގައި. މިއީ އަޅުގަނޑަށް އާ ސަރަހައްދެއް، އެކަމަކު މުޅި ހަފުތާގެ ރިހާސަލްތައް ކޮށް، މޫސުން އެއްބާރުލުން ދެއްވުން އެދި ދުއާ ކުރަމުން މިދަނީ. މިއަދު ވަރަށް ފުރިހަމަ، އަޅުގަނޑަށް ޔަޤީން، ވަރަށް ގިނަ ބެލޫންތައް ފުންމާލާނެކަން. ނަސީބަކުން ކޮންމެ ބެލޫނަކަށް ވެސް ޖިޕެއް ހަވާލުކުރެވިފައި، ތިރިން ފަހަތުން ދެއެވެ. އެހެންވީމާ، އަގާދިރަށް ޖެއްސިޔަސް، އެކަންވެސް ވާނީ."

en: “Absolutely nothing. I was born the Viscount St. Ives, and one day I’ll become the Earl of Greshamsbury. But I come into that title only when my father dies. So it’s a promotion I’m not exactly looking forward to.”
Sesotho: "Ho hang ha ho letho. Ke tsoetsoe e le Viscount St. Ives, 'me ka letsatsi le leng ke tla ba Earl ea Greshamsbury. Empa ke kena ka hare ho lebitso lena feela ha ntate a hlokahala. Kahoo, ke papatso eo ke sa e boneng ka botlalo. "
Yorùbá: "Kò sí nkankan rárá. Wọ́n bí mi ní Viscount St. Ives, àti pé ní ọjọ́ kan mà á di Earl of Greshamsbury. Ṣùgbọ́n ìgbà tí bàbá mi bá kú nìkan ni mo wọ inú àkọ́lé yẹn. Ó jẹ́ ìgbéga tí mi ò fi bẹ́ẹ̀ fojú sọ́nà fún.
Setswana (Tswana): "Go nothing gotlhelele." Ke tshotswe ka letsatsi le le lengwe ke ne ke nna mosukutla wa ga Greshamsbury. Ke ne ke le mo go yone fela fa rre a ne a tlhokafala. Ke ka moo ke sa boneng sepe se ke se lebeletseng pele."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Aita hoê a'e mea. Ua fanauhia vau i Viscount St. Ives, e i te hoê mahana, e riro mai au ei Earl no Greshamsbury. Tera râ, e topa vau i roto i taua ti'araa ra ia pohe ana'e to'u metua tane. No reira, e ohipa teie o ta'u e ore e tia'i nei ".
Maithili: "बिल्कुल किछु नहि। हमर जन्म विस्काउंट सेंट आइव्स मे भेल छल, आ एक दिन हम अर्ल ऑफ ग्रेशमबरी बनि जाएब। मुदा हम ओहि उपाधि मे तखन अबैत छी जखन हमर पिताक मृत्यु भऽ जाइत अछि। तेँ ई एकटा एहन पदोन्नति अछि जकर हम बिल्कुल प्रतीक्षा नहि कऽ रहल छी।
Malagasy: "Tsy misy na inona na inona. Teraka tao amin'ny Viscount St. Ivess aho, ary indray andro any dia ho lasa Earl of Greshamsbury. Rehefa maty anefa ny raiko, vao tonga amin'izany anaram - boninahitra izany aho. Izany no iray amin'ireo zavatra izay tsy azoko antenaina. "
Divehi (Dhivehi): "އެއްވެސް ކަމެއް ނެތް. އަހަރެން އުފަންވީ ވިސްކައުންޓް ސެއިންޓް އައިވްސް އަށް، ކޮންމެވެސް ދުވަހަކުން އަހަރެން ވާނީ އާލް އޮފް ގްރެޝެމްސްބަރީ އަށެވެ. އެކަމަކު އަހަރެން އެ ލަގަބަށް ވަންނަނީ ބައްޕަ މަރުވުމުންނެވެ. އެހެންވީމަ މިއީ އަހަރެން ވަރަށް ބޮޑަށް އިންތިޒާރު ކުރާ ޕްރޮމޯޝަނެއް."

en: “That’s where I was born! You know, right after my mom gave birth, my father bought a ninety-carat yellow diamond at auction from Christie’s and presented it to me at the hospital. It was an extremely rare diamond called the Golden Star, and he renamed it the Golden Martha. It made the front pages of all the newspapers. ‘Billionaire Buys Newborn Daughter Forty-Eight-Million-Dollar Diamond.’ Ever since then, I’ve been fodder for the papers, mainly in Asia. So I understand your problem.”
Sesotho: Mona ke moo ke hlahetseng teng! Ua tseba, hantle ka mor'a hore 'mè oa ka a beleha, ntate o ile a reka taemane e mosehla e mashome a robong-carat ka fantisi e tsoang ho Christie's mme a e hlahisa sepetlele. E ne e le taemane e sa tloaelehang haholo e bitsoang Golden Star, 'me o e reha lebitso la Maretha ea Khauta. E entse maqephe a ka pele a likoranta tsohle. "Billionaire o reka morali ea sa tsoa tsoaloa a le lilemo li 48-000 tsa litaemane." Ho tloha ka nako eo, ke 'nile ka fodder bakeng sa lipampiri, haholo-holo Asia. Ke utloisisa bothata ba hau. "
Yorùbá: "Ibi tí wọ́n bí mi nìyẹn! O mọ̀, lẹ́yìn tí ìyá mi bímọ, bàbá mi ra òkúta iyebíye òféèfé mọ́kàndínlọ́gọ́rùn-ún níbi ìtajà láti Christie's ó sì gbé e fún mi ní ilé ìwòsàn. Ó jẹ́ òkúta iyebíye tí kò wọ́pọ̀ tí wọ́n ń pè ní Golden Star, ó sì yí orúkọ rẹ̀ padà sí Golden Martha. Ó ṣe ojú ìwé iwájú gbogbo àwọn ìwé ìròyìn náà. 'Billionaire ra ọmọbìnrin tuntun ogójì mílíọ̀nù dọ́là Diamond.' Láti ìgbà náà, mo ti ń jẹ oúnjẹ fún àwọn ìwé ìròyìn náà, pàápàá jùlọ ní Asia. Nítorí náà ìṣòro rẹ yé mi."
Setswana (Tswana): "Yono ke yo o tsholetsweng gone jaanong." O a itse gore fa rre a sena go belega, rre o ne a reka taemane ya borobabongwe e e ferabongwe fa a ne a le mo fa a neng a le kwa bookelong mme a mpolelela fa ke le kwa bookelong. E ne e le taemane e e sa tlwaelegang e e bidiwang Golden Star, mme a e bitsa Golden Martha. O ne a dira ditsebe tse di kwa pele tsa makwalodikgang otlhe. 'Rêka ngwana yo o sa tswang go belegwa a le dimilione di le lesome le borobabobedi' - The girl buys of fifty-8 million-million diamond Go tloga ka nako eo, ke ne ka nna le dipampiri tse di neng di le teng, segolobogolo kwa Asia. 'Ke tlhaloganya bothata jwa gago' - I understand your problem
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " I reira to'u fanau-raa-hia ! Ua ite outou, i muri noa iho i to to'u mama fanau-raa-hia, ua hoo mai to'u metua tane i te hoê taiamani re'are'a e iva ahuru ma pae tara i te fare ma'i no Christie e ua faaite mai i te reira ia'u i te fare ma'i. O te hoê ïa taiamani varavara roa tei piihia te Fetia Auro, e ua papai oia i te reira te Mareta Auro. O te mau api matamua ïa o te mau vea atoa. 'Billionaire Buys newborn Daughter Forty-Eight-Million-Dollar taiamani.' Mai reira mai, ua riro vau ei taata haapao i te mau papie, i Asia iho â râ. No reira te taa ra ia'u to oe fifi ".
Maithili: "ओतए हम जन्म लेलहुं! अहां जनैत छी, हमर माँक जन्म देलाक ठीक बाद, हमर पिता क्रिस्टीसँ नीलामीमे नब्बे कैरेटक पीयर हीरा किनलनि आ हमरा अस्पतालमे भेंट कयलनि। ई गोल्डन स्टार नामक एकटा अत्यंत दुर्लभ हीरा छल, आ ओ एकर नाम बदलि गोल्डन मार्था राखि देलनि। इ सभ अखबारक पहिल पन्ना बना देलक। 'अरबपति नवजात बेटी के अड़तालीस मिलियन डॉलर के हीरा खरीदैत अछि। तहियासँ हम मुख्य रूपसँ एशियामे कागजक लेल चारा छी। त हम अहां के समस्या के समझैत छी।
Malagasy: Teo no nahaterahako! Fantatrao, vantany vao teraka ny reniko, dia nividy diamondra mavo 90 karatra ny raiko tamin'ny lavanty avy amin'i Christie ary nanolotra izany tamiko tany amin'ny hopitaly. Diamondra tena tsy fahita firy antsoina hoe Golden Star izy io, ary nanova ny anarany hoe Golden Martha. Nisongadina tamin'ny gazety rehetra izany. "Mividy diamondra valo amby efapolo tapitrisa dolara ilay miliaridera." Hatramin'izay fotoana izay, efa vonona ho an'ny gazety aho, indrindra fa any Azia. Azoko tsara ny olanao."

en: For a moment, the popping of corks high above Marrakech sounded like a fifty-gun salute. The wedding guests shared a toast as the fleet of balloons drifted east toward the rising sun.
Sesotho: Ka motsotsoana, ho hlaha ha li-corks tse phahameng ka holimo marrakech ho utloahala joalo ka salute ea lithunya tse mashome a mahlano. Ba ile ba arolelana toast e le 'ngoe ea libalune tse tsamaeang ka bochabela ho ea letsatsing le chabang.
Yorùbá: Fún ìgbà díẹ̀, yíyọ àwọn corks tí ó ga lókè Marrakech dún bí ìkíni ìbọn àádọ́ta. Àwọn àlejò ìgbéyàwó náà pín ọtí kan bí àwọn bọ́ọ̀lù ṣe ń lọ sí ìlà-oòrùn sí oòrùn tó ń gòkè.

Batho ba ba neng ba le mo lenyalong ba ne ba na le moletlo o o neng o le mo lewatleng fa ba ne ba ya kwa botlhaba go ya kwa botlhaba.

en: “Where did that nose come from? It’s neither Chinese nor English,” she would say as she paraded him in front of one plastic surgeon after another, as each one tried to convince her that he was too young for rhinoplasty and if she would simply be patient he would grow into his nose. Not content, she would fixate on his physique, badgering his endocrinologist about the fact that he wasn’t growing fast enough. He remembered being asked to leave the examining room on one visit when he was thirteen, and the minute he was outside he could hear his mother whispering loudly through the door:
Sesotho: "Nko ee e tsoa kae? Ha se Machaena kapa Senyesemane," o ne a ka re ha a ntse a mo parakisitse ka pel'a ngaka e buoang e 'ngoe ea polasetiki kamora e' ngoe, kaha e mong le e mong a leka ho mo kholisa hore o ne a le monyane haholo bakeng sa rhinoplasty mme haeba a ka ba le mamello feela o ne a tla hola nkong ea hae. Ha e le hantle, o ne a sa tsebe hore na ke eng, o ne a sa khone ho ba le mamello ea 'mele oa hae ka lebaka la hore o ne a sa hōle ka potlako ka ho lekaneng. O ile a hopola hore o ile a kopuoa ho tsoa kamoreng ea ho hlahloba ka ketelo e le 'ngoe ha a le leshome le metso e meraro, 'me motsotso oo a neng a le ka ntle o ne a ka utloa' mè oa hae a ntse a lla haholo ka monyako:
Yorùbá: Níbo ni imú yẹn ti wá? Kì í ṣe Chinese tàbí Gẹ̀ẹ́sì," yóò sọ bí ó ṣe ń rìn níwájú dókítà abẹ ṣiṣu kan lẹ́yìn òmíràn, bí ọ̀kọ̀ọ̀kan wọn ṣe gbìyànjú láti dá a lójú pé ó kéré jù fún rhinoplasty àti pé tí yóò bá ní sùúrù yóò dàgbà sí imú rẹ̀. Kò ní ìtẹ́lọ́rùn, yóò ṣe àtúnṣe lórí ìrísí rẹ̀, yóò bu ẹnu àtẹ́ lu onímọ̀ nípa endocrinologist rẹ̀ nípa òtítọ́ pé kò dàgbà kíákíá tó. Ó rántí pé wọ́n ní kí ó kúrò nínú yàrá àyẹ̀wò ní ìbẹ̀wò kan nígbà tí ó wà ní ọmọ ọdún mẹ́tàlá, àti pé ní ìṣẹ́jú tí ó wà níta ó gbọ́ tí ìyá rẹ̀ ń sọ̀rọ̀ sókè láti ẹnu ọ̀nà:
Setswana (Tswana): 'O tswa kae?' - Where did that nose came from? "Ga go na se-China kgotsa Seesemane," o ne a ka re fa a ne a le kwa pele ga ngaka e nngwe ya polasetiki morago ga e nngwe, jaaka mongwe le mongwe a ne a leka go mo kgodisa gore o ne a le monnye thata ka rhinoplasty mme fa a ka nna pelotelele fela gore o tla gola mo nkong ya gagwe. O ne a sa itse gore o ne a le mo seemong se a neng a se dira, o ne a sa kgone go gola ka bonako gore a se ka a gola ka bonako. O ne a gakologelwa gore o ne a kopa go tswa mo phaposing e e tlhatlhobilweng fa a ne a le 13, mme motsotso oo a neng a le kwa ntle o ne a kgona go utlwa mmaagwe a lela thata ka lebati.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " No hea mai taua ihu ra ? E ere i te reo Tinito e aore râ, i te reo Peretane ", ta'na ïa parau a faaite ai oia ia'na i mua i te hoê taote tapu uraina i muri a'e i te tahi, a tamata ai te taata tata'itahi i te haapapû ia'na e, e mea apî roa oia no te rhinoplasty, e mai te mea e, e faaoroma'i noa oia, e tupu ïa oia i te rahi i roto i to'na ihu. Ma te ore e mauruuru, e haamau oia i to ' na tino i nia i to ' na tino, ma te faaino i to ' na taote i te pae o te mau uaua no te mea aita o ' na e tupu oioi ra. Te haamana'o ra oia i to'na ani-raa-hia ia haere i rapae i te piha hi'opo'araa i te hoê tere to'na i te ahuru ma toruraa o to'na matahiti, e i te minuti tei rapae oia, ua faaroo oia i to'na metua vahine i te muhumuhuraa ma te reo puai na roto i te opani :
Maithili: "ओ नाक कतए सं आयल? ई न त चीनी अछि आ ने अङ्ग्रेजी," ओ हुनका एकक बाद एक प्लास्टिक सर्जनक सोझाँ घुमाबैत कहैत छलीह, किएक तँ सभगोटे हुनका मनयबाक प्रयास करैत छलाह जे ओ राइनोप्लास्टीक लेल बहुत छोट छथि आ जँ ओ बस धैर्य राखत तँ ओ ओकर नाकमे बढ़ि जायत। संतुष्ट नहि, ओ हुनक शरीरपर स्थिर भऽ जाइत छलीह, हुनक एंडोक्रिनोलॉजिस्टकेँ एहि तथ्यक बारेमे बतबैत छलीह जे ओ पर्याप्त तेजीसँ नहि बढ़ि रहल छलाह। हुनका मोन पड़लनि जे जखन ओ तेरह वर्षक छलाह तखन हुनका एकटा यात्रामे जाँच कक्षसँ बाहर निकलबाक लेल कहल गेल छलनि, आ जाहि क्षण ओ बाहर छलाह ओ अपन मायकेँ दरवाजासँ जोरसँ फुसफुसाबैत सुनि सकैत छलाह:

Divehi (Dhivehi): އެ ނޭފަތް އައީ ކޮންތަނަކުން ހެއްޔެވެ؟ އެއީ ޗައިނީޒް ވެސް އަދި އިނގިރޭސި ވެސް ނޫން،" އެއް ޕްލާސްޓިކް ސާޖަނަކަށް ފަހު އަނެއް ސާޖަނެއްގެ ކުރިމަތީގައި އޭނާ ޕެރޭޑް ކުރަމުން ދިޔަ އިރު، ކޮންމެ މީހަކު ވެސް އޭނާ އަކީ ރައިނޯޕްލާސްޓީ އަށް މާ ޒުވާން ކުއްޖެއް ކަން ވިސްނައިދޭން މަސައްކަތް ކުރަމުން ދިޔަ އިރު، އޭނާ ކެތްތެރިވެއްޖެ ނަމަ އޭނާގެ ނޭފަތަށް ބޮޑުވާނެ އެވެ. ހިތްހަމަ ނުޖެހޭ، އޭނާ އޭނާގެ ހަށިގަނޑަށް ފިކްސްކޮށް، އޭނާގެ އެންޑޯކްރައިނޮލޮޖިސްޓު ގެ ނަޒަރުގައި އޭނާ އެހާ ބާރަށް ކުރިއަރަމުން ނުދާކަން ބެޖް ކޮށްލާނެ އެވެ. އުމުރުން ތޭރަ އަހަރުގައި އެއް ޒިޔާރަތެއްގައި އިމްތިހާނު ކުރާ ކޮޓަރިން ނުކުތުމަށް އެންގި ހަނދާންވުމުން ބޭރުގައި ހުރި ވަގުތު ދޮރުން މަންމަ ބާރު ބާރަށް ހަޅޭއްލަވައިގަތް އަޑު އިވުނެވެ.

en: “Funny you should ask. I went into my treatment room, and this huge man with a gigantic belly protruding over his loincloth told me to take off all my clothes and lie on the ground. So I obeyed. Then he pressed my face to the cold, wet marble and proceeded to twist me around like a rag doll and cracked every bone in my body, bones I didn’t even know I possessed. I feel like minced meat and I think I’m scarred for life.”

en: “It’s fine. Look, it’s hard to talk about all this without sounding like some entitled prat. I know I’m bloody lucky, but it’s always been difficult for me to make real friends—people who genuinely want to connect with me, rather than with my title or my country house or my family’s resorts. I don’t usually complain like this, but I’m being completely open with you because I think you’ll understand.”

Hangata ha ke tletleba joalo ka sena, empa ke ntse ke bulehetse ka botlalo le uena hobane ke nahana hore u tla utloisisa. "

Mo mọ̀ pé oríire ni mí, ṣùgbọ́n ó máa ń ṣòro fún mi láti jẹ́ ọ̀rẹ́ gidi - àwọn ènìyàn tí wọ́n fẹ́ so pọ̀ pẹ̀lú mi lóòótọ́, dípò pẹ̀lú àkọlé mi tàbí ilé ìgbèríyìn mi tàbí ibi ìgbafẹ́ ẹbí mi. Mi ò kì í sábà ṣàròyé báyìí, ṣùgbọ́n mo ń ṣí sílẹ̀ pátápátá pẹ̀lú rẹ nítorí mo lérò pé yóò yé ọ."
Setswana (Tswana): "Go siame. Le fa go ntse jalo, go thata go bua ka dilo tseno tsotlhe ntle le go bua fela jaaka motho yo o nang le tshwanelo. en: “No, this area of Beverly Hills is called ‘the Flats’ because it’s on flat land, as opposed to where I was just driving you up in the hills. It’s actually the most desirable part, super-high demand. If any of these houses come onto the market, they’re snapped up within hours of the listing going live.”
Sesotho: "Che, sebaka sena sa Beverly Hills se bitsoa 'Flats' hobane se naheng e bataletseng, ho fapana le moo ke neng ke u khanna maralla. Ha e le hantle ke karolo e lakatsehang ka ho fetesisa, tlhoko e phahameng haholo. Haeba leha e le efe ea matlo ana e fihla 'marakeng, ba tla nka nako e ka tlase ho lihora tse ngata tsa lenane la bophelo. "
Yorùbá: "Rárá, agbègbè Beverly Hills yìí ni wọ́n ń pè ní 'the Flats' nítorí pé ó wà lórí ilẹ̀ pẹlẹbẹ, gẹ́gẹ́ bí ìdàkejì ibi tí mo kàn ń gbé ọ sókè ní àwọn òkè. Ó jẹ́ apá tí ó wuni jùlọ, ìbéèrè tó ga jù. Tí èyíkéyìí nínú àwọn ilé wọ̀nyí bá wá sí ọjà, wọ́n máa gbà wọ́n láàárín wákàtí díẹ̀ lẹ́yìn tí àtòjọ náà ń lọ láàyè."
Setswana (Tswana): "Nnyaa, lefelo leno la Beverly Hills le bidiwa 'Flats' ka gonne e le mo lefatsheng le le sephara, go na le moo ke neng ke go kgweetsa gone mo maratong. Lololololololololololololololololololololololololo that is the mostdesirable, super demander. Fa e le gore go na le mongwe wa ba ba nang le matlo a a ntseng jalo, ba tla nna mo malatsing a diura di le dintsi ba ntse ba tshela."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Aita, ua piihia teie vahi no Beverly Hills 'te mau Flats' no te mea tei ni'a te reira i te fenua parahurahu, e mea taa ê roa i te vahi ta'u e faahoro ra ia oe i ni'a i te mau aivi. O te tuhaa hinaaro-roa-hia a'e ïa, te mea hinaaro-roa-hia a'e. Mai te mea e, e tae mai te hoê o teie mau fare i ni'a i te matete, e mau roa ïa te reira i roto noa i te mau hora o te tabula ohipa ".
Maithili: "नहि, बेवर्ली हिल्सक एहि क्षेत्रकेँ 'द फ्लैट्स' कहल जाइत अछि किएक तँ ई समतल भूमि पर अछि, जतय हम अहाँकेँ पहाड़ीमे लऽ जा रहल छलहुँ। ई वास्तवमे सबसँ वांछनीय भाग अछि, अति-उच्च माँग। जँ एहिमेसँ कोनो घर बजारमे आबि जाइत अछि तँ सूचीकरणक लाइव होयबाक किछु घंटाक भीतर ओकरा तोड़ि देल जाइत अछि।"

Raha ny marina dia io no tena ilaina indrindra, ny tinady ambony indrindra. en: “My mother keeps appearing in the strangest places in my dreams, but I can never understand a thing she’s saying. I wish we could have a normal conversation as two adults. I’d love to hear her voice again. Sometimes I think I’ve forgotten what she sounds like. It’d be nice just to be able to call her up and hear a good yarn.”
Sesotho: "Mme oa ka o lula a hlaha libakeng tse makatsang ka ho fetesisa litorong tsa ka, empa ha ke utloisise ntho eo a e buang. Ke lakatsa eka re ka ba le puisano e tloaelehileng joalo ka batho ba baholo ba babeli. Ke thabela ho utloa lentsoe la hae hape. Ka linako tse ling ke nahana hore ke lebetse seo a se utloang. Ho ka ba monate ho mo letsetsa le ho utloa lentsoe le monate. "
Yorùbá: "Iya mi n farahan ni awọn aaye ajeji julọ ninu awọn ala mi, ṣugbọn emi ko loye ohun ti o n sọ. Ó wù mí kí á ní ìtàkùrọ̀sọ tí ó dára gẹ́gẹ́ bí àgbàlagbà méjì. Mà á nífẹ̀ẹ́ láti gbọ́ ohùn rẹ̀ lẹ́ẹ̀kan si. Nígbà mìíràn mo rò pé mo ti gbàgbé bí ó ṣe dún. Ó máa dára láti lè pè é kí o sì gbọ́ òwú gidi."
Setswana (Tswana): "Ke ne ke sa kgone go bona gore go na le sengwe se nka se buang, mme ga ke kgone go tlhaloganya sengwe se a se buang. Ke eletsa gore re nne le puisano e e tlwaelegileng jaaka bagolo ba le babedi. Ke rata go utlwa lentswe la gagwe gape. Ka dinako tse dingwe ke lebala se a se utlwang. Go ka bo go le monate go bua le ene a bo a mo utlwa a le monate." - Le fa go ntse jalo, o ka mo raya a re: "Go siame go bua le ene."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Ua tamau noa to'u metua vahine i te ti'a i te mau vahi huru ê roa i roto i ta'u mau moemoea, aita râ vau i taa i te hoê mea ta'na e parau ra. Te hinaaro nei au e faatupu i te hoê aparauraa matauhia e e piti taata paari. E mea au roa na'u ia faaroo faahou i to'na reo. I te tahi mau taime, e mana'o vau e ua moehia ia ' u to ' na huru. E mea au roa ia pii ia'na e ia faaroo i te hoê popo maitai ".

en: “When I went to Miami last December, I noticed that every billionaire art collector had an artist staying at their house. The artists were all sucking up like crazy, following them around everywhere, and I thought, They’re like cute little pets, art pets. So I’m gonna have a different one every month. I feed them and give them a place to stay, and in return I get a free artwork from a hot artist. The last one who stayed with me, I hated her painting, but I flipped it for half a mil.”
Sesotho: "Ha ke ea Miami ka December e fetileng, ke ile ka hlokomela hore 'mokelli e mong le e mong oa mesebetsi ea libilione o ne a e-na le moetsi oa litšoantšo ea lulang hae. Kaofela ha bona ba ne ba ntse ba hlanya joaloka bohlanya, ba li latela hohle, 'me ke nahana hore, li tšoana le liphoofolo tse ruuoang lapeng tse nyane, liphoofolo tse ruuoang lapeng. Ke batla ho ba le nako e fapaneng khoeli le khoeli. Ke ba fepa le ho ba fa sebaka sa ho lula, 'me ka mor'a moo ke fumana bonono bo sa lefelloeng ho moetsi ea chesang. Ea ileng a lula le 'na, ke hloile pente ea hae, empa ke e flipped ka halofo ea limilimithara. "
Yorùbá: "Nígbà tí mo lọ sí Miami ní oṣù Kejìlá tó kọjá, mo ṣàkíyèsí pé gbogbo olùkó iṣẹ́ ọnà ọlọ́rọ̀ bilionu ló ní oníṣẹ́-ọnà kan tí ó ń gbé ní ilé wọn. Gbogbo àwọn oníṣẹ́-ọnà náà ń bínú bí aṣiwèrè, tí wọ́n ń tẹ̀lé wọn káàkiri níbi gbogbo, mo sì rò pé, wọ́n dàbí ẹran ọ̀sìn kékeré tó rẹwà, àwọn ẹran ọ̀sìn iṣẹ́-ọnà. Nítorí náà mà á ní òmíràn lóṣooṣù. Mo bọ́ wọn mo sì fún wọn ní ààyè láti dúró sí, àti pé ní ìdápadà mo gba iṣẹ́ ọnà ọ̀fẹ́ lọ́wọ́ oníṣẹ́-ọnà gbígbóná. Ẹni tí ó kẹ́yìn tí ó dúró tì mí, mo kórìíra àwòrán rẹ̀, ṣùgbọ́n mo yí i padà fún ìdajì mil."
Setswana (Tswana): "Fa ke ne ke ya kwa Mexico ka Sedimonthole ngogola, ke ne ka lemoga gore motaki mongwe le mongwe wa di-billionaire o ne a nna mo ntlong ya gagwe. Batho botlhe ba ba neng ba le mo tseleng ba ne ba le mo tseleng e e sa siamang, mme ke ne ke akanya gore ba tshwana le diphologolo tse di potlana tse di potlana. Ke batla go patela kgwedi le kgwedi. Ke ba fepa le go ba naya lefelo le ba ka nnang mo go lone, mme fa ke boa ke bona tiro ya go dira tiro e e sa dueleng. Yo o neng a setse a na le nna, ke ne ke mo tlhoile, mme ke ne ka mo lalela ka di-kilometara."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " I to'u haereraa i Miami i te ava'e titema i ma'iri a'e nei, ua ite au e te vai nei ta te mau taata peni hoho'a tata'itahi te hoê hoho'a peni e faaea ra i to ratou fare. Ua huti pauroa te feia peni hoho'a mai te maamaa ra te huru, ma te apee ia ratou i te mau vahi atoa, e ua mana'o vau e, e au ratou i te mau animala nainai, te mau animala aravihi. No reira, e fana'o vau i te hoê ohipa taa ê i te mau ava'e atoa. E faaamu vau ia ratou e e horo'a vau i te hoê vahi faaearaa no ratou, e ei faaho'iraa, e farii au i te hoê ohipa rima î na te hoê taata peni hoho'a ve'ave'a. Te taata hopea tei faaea mai i piha'i iho ia'u, e mea au ore roa na'u ta'na hoho'a peni, tera râ, ua taviri au i te reira no te hoê afa maile ".
Maithili: "जखन हम पछिला दिसम्बरमे मियामी गेलहुँ तखन हम देखलहुँ जे प्रत्येक अरबपति कला संग्राहकक घरमे एकटा कलाकार रहैत छथि। कलाकार सभ पागल जकाँ चूसि रहल छलाह, सभ ठाम हुनकासभक पीछा कऽ रहल छलाह, आ हम सोचलहुँ, ओ सभ प्यारा छोट पालतू जानवर, कला पालतू जानवर जकाँ छथि। त हम हर महीना एकटा अलग लेबए जा रहल छी। हम हुनका सभकेँ खुआबैत छी आ रहबाक लेल जगह दैत छी, आ बदलामे हमरा एकटा हॉट आर्टिस्टसँ मुफ्त कलाकृति भेटैत अछि। अंतिम जे हमरा सङ्ग रहल, हमरा हुनक चित्रकलासँ नफरत छल, मुदा हम एकरा आधा मिलियनमे पलटि देलहुँ।"
Malagasy: "Rehefa nandeha tany Miami aho tamin'ny volana Desambra lasa teo, dia nahatsikaritra fa ny mpanangona zavakanto an-davitrisany rehetra dia manana mpanakanto mipetraka ao an-tranony. Ninonoka toy ny adala avokoa ireo mpanakanto, nanaraka azy ireo na aiza na aiza, ary nieritreritra aho hoe, toy ny biby fiompy kely mahafatifaty izy ireo, biby an-trano ara-javakanto. Manana iray hafa aho isam-bolana. Manome sakafo azy ireo aho ary manome azy ireo toerana hipetrahana, ary ho setrin'izany dia mahazo zavakanto maimaim-poana avy amin'ny mpanakanto mafana iray aho. Ny farany nijanona niaraka tamiko, halako ny sary hosodokony, saingy navadiko antsasaka mil izany."
Divehi (Dhivehi): "މިދިޔަ ޑިސެމްބަރު މަހު މަޔާމީއަށް ދިޔައިރު އަޅުގަނޑަށް ފާހަގަކުރެވުނީ ކޮންމެ ބިލިއަނަރު އާޓް ކަލެކްޓަރެއްގެ ގޭގައި އާޓިސްޓެއް އުޅޭކަން. އާޓިސްޓުން އެންމެން ވެސް މޮޔައެއް ފަދައިން ބޮސްދެމުން ދިޔައިރު، ހުރިހާ ދިމާލަކުން ވެސް އެމީހުންގެ ފަހަތުން އެމީހުންގެ ފަހަތުން ދިޔައިރު، އަހަރެން ހީކުރީ، އެމީހުންނަކީ ކިއުޓް ލިޓްލް ޕެޓްސް، އާޓް ޕެޓްސް ފަދަ ބައެކެވެ. އެހެންވީމާ، ކޮންމެ މަހަކު ވެސް އަޅުގަނޑަށް ތަފާތު އެއްޗެހި ލިބޭނެ. އެކުދިންނަށް ކާންދީ، ތިބޭނެ ތަނެއް ދީ، އޭގެ ބަދަލުގައި ހޮޓް އާޓިސްޓެއްގެ އަތުން ހިލޭ އާޓްވޯކެއް ލިބެއެވެ. އެންމެ ފަހުން އަހަރެންނާ އެކު މަޑުކުރި މީހާ އޭނާގެ ކުރެހުމަށް ނަފްރަތު ކުރި ނަމަވެސް ބައިމިލް ވަންދެން ފުރޮޅާލީމެވެ.

Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " E mau parau huna ana'e te reira, te hoê râ o te reira, o te feti'a rahi roa a'e ïa i te ao nei. E faaroo oe i te mau mea atoa no ni'a i te reira ia tae i te taime ".

en: “I’m guessing it was a very posh school. Things are different these days. We’ve got our problems, but for the most part it’s easier nowadays to be accepted.”
Sesotho: "Ke ne ke nahana hore e ne e le sekolo se setle haholo. Matsatsing ana, lintho li fapane. Re na le mathata a rōna, empa ka lehlakoreng le leng ho le bonolo ho feta kajeno ho amoheloa. "
Yorùbá: "Mo ro pe o jẹ ile-iwe posh pupọ. Nǹkan yàtọ̀ lẹ́nu ọjọ́ mẹ́ta yìí. A ní àwọn ìṣòro wa, ṣùgbọ́n fún ọ̀pọ̀lọpọ̀ ìgbà ó rọrùn lóde òní láti gbà."
Setswana (Tswana): 'Ke ne ke ithaya ke re e ne e le sekolo se se potlana' - It was a very good school Dilo di a farologana le tsone mo malatsing ano. Re na le mathata a rona, mme ka ntlha ya bontsi jwa gompieno go ka nna motlhofo gore re amogelwe."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Te mana'o nei au e, e fare haapiiraa tuarua roa teie. E mea taa ê te mau mea i teie mahana. Te vai ra to tatou mau fifi, tera râ, i te rahiraa o te taime, e mea ohie a'e ia farii i te reira ".
Maithili: "हम अनुमान लगा रहल छी जे ई बहुत पॉश स्कूल छल। आजुक दिन स्थिति अलग अछि। हमरासभकेँ अपन समस्या भेटल अछि, मुदा अधिकांश भागक लेल आइ-काल्हि एकरा स्वीकार करब आसान अछि।"
Malagasy: "Heveriko fa sekoly tena tsara io. Hafa ny toe-draharaha amin'izao andro izao. Manana olana izahay, saingy amin'ny ankapobeny dia mora kokoa ny manaiky izany amin'izao fotoana izao. "
Divehi (Dhivehi): "އަޅުގަނޑަށް ހީވަނީ އެއީ ވަރަށް ޕޮޝް ސްކޫލެއް ކަމަށް. މިދުވަސްވަރު ކަންކަން ތަފާތެވެ. އަޅުގަނޑުމެންނަށް މައްސަލަތަކެއް އެބަހުރި، އެކަމަކު ގިނަ ފަހަރަށް މިއަދު ޤަބޫލުކުރަން ފަސޭހަވޭ."

en: “You know, instead of throwing a party or throwing your money around, maybe you ought to think about being with your father. All he wants to do is spend time with you. He really doesn’t have much longer, and I guarantee you all the money in the world will never bring him back.”
Sesotho: "O a tseba, ho ena le ho lahlela mokga kapa ho lahlela tjhelete ya hao ho potoloha, mohlomong o lokela ho nahana ka ho ba le ntatao. Sohle seo a batlang ho se etsa ke ho qeta nako le uena. Ha a na nako e teletsana, 'me ke u tiisetsa hore chelete eohle lefatšeng e ke ke ea mo khutlisetsa. "
Yorùbá: "O mọ̀, dípò kí o ṣe ayẹyẹ tàbí kí o fi owó rẹ káàkiri, bóyá ó yẹ kí o ronú nípa wíwà pẹ̀lú bàbá rẹ. Gbogbo ohun tí ó fẹ́ ṣe ni kí ó lo àkókò pẹ̀lú rẹ. Kò ní púpọ̀ mọ́, mo sì fi dá ọ lójú pé gbogbo owó ayé kò ní mú un padà wá láéláé."
Setswana (Tswana): "Go na le gore o itse gore go na le go latlhela madi kgotsa go latlhela madi a gago mo go one, gongwe o tshwanetse go akanya ka go nna le rre. Se a se dirang ke go fetsa nako le wena. Ga a na lobaka lo loleele, mme ke go tlhomamisetsa gore o tla nna le madi otlhe a a mo lefatsheng."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Ua ite oe, eiaha e taora i te hoê arearearaa e aore râ e taora i ta oe moni i te hiti, peneia'e e ti'a ia oe ia feruri ia parahi i piha'i iho i to oe metua tane. Te mea noa ta ' na e hinaaro e rave, o te horoaraa ïa i te taime no outou. Aita ta'na e moni faahou, e te haapapû atu nei au ia outou e, eita te taatoaraa o te moni i te ao nei e faaho'i mai ia'na ".
Maithili: "अहां जनैत छी, पार्टी फेंकय या अपन पाइ के आसपास फेंकय के बदला शायद अहाँके अपन पिता के संग रहय के बारे मे सोचय के चाही। ओ बस अहां के संग समय बिताना चाहैत छथि। हुनका लग सचमुच बेसी समय नहि अछि, आ हम गारंटी दैत छी जे दुनियाक सभ पाइ ओकरा कहियो वापिस नहि आओत।"

en: “Post-traumatic wealth disorder. It’s a real thing. My children had it when we had to move into a temporary house in Brentwood after the Malibu fire destroyed our compound. They just could not cope with the shame of being in Brentwood. And everything about that house depressed them—the pool, the tennis court, the giant outdoor trampoline. That’s when my daughter tried to get a face tattoo and my son started cutting himself.”
Sesotho: Post-Traumatic wealth disorder. ho Ke ntho ea sebele. Bana ba ka ba ne ba e-na le eona ha re tlameha ho fallela ntlong ea nakoana ho Brentwood kamora hore mollo oa Malibu o senye motsoako oa rona. Ba ne ba sa khone ho mamella lihlong tsa ho ba brentwood. 'Me ntho e' ngoe le e 'ngoe e mabapi le ntlo eo e ile ea ba sithabetse ka har'a letamo, lekhotla la tenese, le leholo le ka ntle trampoline. Ke nakong eo morali oa ka a neng a leka ho fumana tattoo ea sefahleho 'me mora oa ka a qala ho itlhatsoa. "
Yorùbá: "Àìsàn ọrọ̀ lẹ́yìn ìpọ́njú. Ohun gidi ni. Àwọn ọmọ mi ní i nígbà tí a ní láti kó lọ sí ilé ìgbà díẹ̀ ní Brentwood lẹ́yìn tí iná Malibu ba ilé wa jẹ́. Wọn kò kàn lè kojú ìtìjú wíwà ní Brentwood. Àti pé gbogbo nkan nípa ilé yẹn bà wọ́n nínú jẹ́ - odò ìwẹ̀, pápá tẹníìsì, trampoline ńlá ìta. Ìgbà yẹn ni ọmọbìnrin mi gbìyànjú láti gba ẹ̀ṣọ́ ojú tí ọmọkùnrin mi sì bẹ̀rẹ̀ sí ní gé ara rẹ̀."
Setswana (Tswana): Post-Traumatic wealth bone disorder. Ya that's a real thing. Re ne ra tshwanelwa ke go tsena mo ntlong e e neng e le gaufi le go ya go nna mo ntlong e e neng e le teng fa re sena go thubega ga rona. Ba ne ba sa kgone go itshokela ditlhong tsa go nna kwa Ville. Mme sengwe le sengwe se se neng se ba tshwenya thata ke gore ba ne ba tshwentswe ke motlhaba, kgotla ya tenese, e e neng e le ya kwa ntle. Ke sone se ke neng ke se dira fa morwadiake a ne a leka go nna le tattoo ya sefatlhego mme morwaake a simolola go itshegaka."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Te fifi i te pae no te moni. E ohipa mau te reira. Ua farii ta'u mau tamarii i te reira i te taime a titauhia ai ia matou ia haere i roto i te hoê fare no te hoê tau poto i Brentwood i muri a'e i te paapaaraa ta matou fare pureraa i te auahi no Malibu. Aita roa ' tu ratou i nehenehe e faaruru i te haama o te faaearaa i Brentwood. E ua haape'ape'a te mau mea atoa no ni'a i taua fare ra—te vahi hopuraa pape, te tahua huiraa popo, te vahi hautiraa popo rahi i rapae. I reira ta'u tamahine i te tamataraa i te haru i te hoê tapo'i mata e ua haamata ta'u tamaiti i te tapu ia'na iho ".
Maithili: "पोस्ट-ट्रॉमेटिक वेल्थ डिसऑर्डर। ई वास्तव मे बात अछि। मालिबूक आगि हमर परिसर नष्ट भेलाक बाद हमरा ब्रेंटवुडक एकटा अस्थायी घरमे जाय पड़ल, तखन हमर बच्चासभकेँ ई भेल। ब्रेंटवुडमे रहबाक शर्मक सामना ओ सभ नहि कऽ सकलाह। आ ओहि घरक सब किछु हुनका सभकेँ उदास कऽ देलक - पूल, टेनिस कोर्ट, विशाल आउटडोर ट्रैम्पोलिन। तखन हमर बेटी फेस टैटू बनयबाक कोशिश केलक आ हमर बेटा अपनाकेँ काटय लागल।"

en: She arrived at last at Freddy’s mansion and waited as the ornate iron gates opened slowly. As she pulled into the immaculately tiled driveway, she saw a man standing under the ivy-clad porte cochere and thought she must be hallucinating. She slammed on her brakes, rushed out of the car, and ran up the steps, right into Rufus’s arms.
Sesotho: Qetellong o ile a fihla ntlong ea Freddy 'me a leta ha liheke tsa tšepe tsa ornate li butsoe butle. Ha a ntse a kena ka har'a tsela e se nang sekoli, o ile a bona monna ea emeng ka tlas'a koung ea ivy-clad cochere mme a nahana hore o tlameha ho hallucinating. O ile a matha ka koloing, a matha ka maoto a hae, a matha ka maoto, a kena ka har'a lihlomo tsa Rufus.
Yorùbá: Ó dé gbẹ̀yìn ní ilé Freddy ó sì dúró bí àwọn ẹnubodè irin ọ̀ṣọ́ ṣe ṣí díẹ̀díẹ̀. Bí ó ṣe wọ ọ̀nà tí kò ní àbàwọ́n, ó rí ọkùnrin kan tí ó dúró lábẹ́ cochere porte tí ó wọ ivy tí ó sì rò pé ó gbọ́dọ̀ máa ṣe ìfọwọ́sowọ́pọ̀. Ó gbá ibẹ̀rẹ̀kì rẹ̀ mọ́lẹ̀, ó sáré jáde kúrò nínú ọkọ̀ ayọ́kẹ́lẹ́ náà, ó sì sáré gòkè lọ, sí ọwọ́ Rufus.
Setswana (Tswana): O ne a goroga kwa ntlong ya ga Freddy mme a leta fa dikgoro tsa tshipi di bulega ka bonya. O ne a tabogela mo koloing ya gagwe, mme a tabogela kwa tlase, a ya kwa tlase mo sethunyang sa gagwe.

en: It was the wildest, most desolate road either of them had ever been on, just black tar and flat gray scrub on both sides of the highway as far as the eye could see. Far off on the horizon, a tiny speck morphed slowly into something bigger and bigger, and as they drew nearer Eden suddenly caught sight of it:
Sesotho: E ne e le tsela e hlaha ka ho fetisisa, e lesupi ka ho fetisisa e kileng ea e-ba teng, feela tar e ntšo le scrub e boreleli mahlakoreng ka bobeli a tsela e kholo ho ea fihla leihlong. ʻO ka hoʻoponopono ʻana i ka hoʻoponopono ʻana i ka hoʻokele ʻana i ka ʻikepili a me ka hoʻoponopono ʻana:
Yorùbá: Ó jẹ́ ọ̀nà tí ó burú jùlọ, tí ó ti di ahoro jùlọ tí ọ̀kankan nínú wọn ti wà lórí rẹ̀ rí, tar dúdú nìkan àti ẹ̀gbẹ́ aláwọ̀ eérú pẹlẹbẹ ní ẹ̀gbẹ́ méjèèjì ọ̀nà ọ̀nà bí ojú ṣe lè rí i. Ó jìnnà sí ojú ọ̀run, speck kékeré kan yí padà díẹ̀díẹ̀ sí nkan tí ó tóbi tí ó sì tóbi, àti pé bí wọ́n ṣe súnmọ́ Eden lójijì rí i:
Setswana (Tswana): E ne e le tsela e e senyegileng go gaisa e nngwe ya tsone e ne e kile ya nna teng, go ne go le bontsho fela le go sweufala mo matlhakoreng a mabedi a tsela go ya bokgakaleng jo bo ka bonang. Ka bonako fela fa go ne go na le sengwe se sennye se se maatla le se segolo, se segolo thata, mme ka bonako fela fa ba sena go atamela Kwa Edene, ba ne ba se bona.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): O te purumu oviri roa ' ' e ïa e te ano roa ' ' e i vai a'enei i nia i te purumu, te tar ereere e te rehu parahurahu i na pae e piti o te purumu rahi e tae roa ' tu i te vahi ta te mata e nehenehe e ite. I te atea ê roa i te iriatai, e hee mǎrû noa mai te hoê hu'a tao'a iti i roto i te hoê mea rahi a'e e te rahi a'e, e a piri noa ' tu ai ratou i Edene, ua ite a'era ratou i te reira:

en: “Heavens, no. Remember, we had never met before and I was probably the last person on earth she wanted to run into, but she had no choice. She was at the best cancer center in the world, and I was randomly assigned to her. It was a complete coincidence. Serendipity, actually.”
Sesotho: Hahahahha, no. Hopola, ha ho mohla re kileng ra kopana le pele mme mohlomong ke motho oa ho qetela lefatšeng eo a neng a batla ho matha ho eona, empa o ne a sena khetho. O ne a le setsing se setle ka ho fetisisa sa kankere lefatšeng, 'me ka tšohanyetso ke ile ka mo fuoa. E ne e le ntho e iketsahalle feela. Serendipity, ehlile. "
Yorùbá: "Heavens, no. ì Rántí, a kò tíì pàdé rí àti pé ó ṣe é ṣe kí èmi ni ẹni ìkẹyìn láyé tí ó fẹ́ sáré wọlé, ṣùgbọ́n kò ní àṣàyàn mìíràn. Ó wà ní ibùdó àrùn jẹjẹrẹ tó dára jùlọ ní àgbáyé, wọ́n sì yàn mí fún un láìròtẹ́lẹ̀. Ìṣẹ̀lẹ̀ pátápátá ni. Serendipity, lóòótọ́."

Divehi (Dhivehi): "ހެވަންސް، ނޯ. ހަނދާން ބަހައްޓަންވީ، މީގެ ކުރިން އަހަންނާ ބައްދަލުވެފައި ނުވާކަމަށާއި، އޭނާ ދުވަން ބޭނުންވި ދުނިޔެމަތީގައި ހުރި އެންމެ ފަހު މީހަކީ އަހަރެން ކަމަށް ވެދާނެކަމަށާއި، ނަމަވެސް އެކަމަނާއަށް އިތުރު ގޮތެއް ނެތެވެ. ދުނިޔޭގައި ހުރި އެންމެ މޮޅު ކެންސަރު ސެންޓަރުގައި އެކަމަނާ ހުންނެވިއިރު، ރޭންޑަމްކޮށް އެކަމަނާއާ އަޅުގަނޑާ ޙަވާލުކުރެވުނެވެ. އެއީ މުޅިން އިއްތިފާގެއް. ސެރެންޑިޕިޓީ، ހަގީގަތުގައި."

en: “Not in the least. She was so very brave, your mother. I pretended not to know who she was—I sensed this was what she wanted—but after a few weeks she suddenly announced that she needed to go back to Vancouver and couldn’t finish her course of chemo and radiation. I pressed her to stay, seeing that the treatments were working, and that’s when she broke down and confessed to me that she needed to return because she had been away far too long from her child. My brother’s child. And that’s when I told her I had known all along who she was and would keep her secret safe. I convinced her to remain in Houston and to send for you.”
Sesotho: Kapa bonyane ha ho joalo. O ne a le sebete haholo, mmao. Ke ne ke nahana hore ha ke tsebe hore na ke mang eo a neng a e-na le eona,' me ka mor'a libeke tse 'maloa o ile a phatlalatsa hore o hloka ho khutlela Vancouver mme a sitoa ho qeta mokhoa oa hae oa chemo le radiation. Ke ile ka mo hatella hore a lule, ka bona hore liphekolo li sebetsa, 'me ke ha a robeha' me a ipolela hore o hloka ho khutla hobane o ne a le hole haholo le ngoana oa hae. Mora oa mor'abo rōna. Ke ile ka mo joetsa hore na ke mang ea neng a le haufi le hore na ke mang mme o tla mo boloka a sireletsehile. Ke ile ka etsa bonnete ba hore o tla lula houston le ho u romela. "
Yorùbá: "Ko si ninu awọn ti o kere ju. Akínkanjú ni ó jẹ́, ìyá rẹ. Mo díbọ́n pé mi ò mọ ẹni tí ó jẹ́ - mo mọ̀ pé ohun tí ó fẹ́ nìyí - ṣùgbọ́n lẹ́yìn ọ̀sẹ̀ díẹ̀ ó kéde lójijì pé ó ní láti padà sí Vancouver kò sì lè parí ọ̀nà ìtọ́jú kẹ́míkà àti ìgbóná rẹ̀. Mo tẹ̀ ẹ́ láti dúró, mo rí i pé àwọn ìtọ́jú náà ń ṣiṣẹ́, àti pé ìgbà yẹn ni ó wó lulẹ̀ tí ó sì jẹ́wọ́ fún mi pé ó ní láti padà nítorí pé ó ti jìnnà sí ọmọ rẹ̀. Ọmọ ẹ̀gbọ́n mi ọkùnrin. Àti pé ìgbà yẹn ni mo sọ fún un pé mo ti mọ ẹni tí ó jẹ́ àti pé mà á dáàbò bo àṣírí rẹ̀. Mo mú un dá a lójú pé kó dúró sí Houston kí ó sì rán ẹ lọ."
Setswana (Tswana): "Notshe least." O ne a le pelokgale thata, mma. Ke ne ke sa itse gore ke eng se a neng a se batla, mme morago ga dibeke di le mmalwa, o ne a tlhalosa gore o ne a tshwanelwa ke go boela kwa Se-Burg mme a se ka a kgona go ya kwa go ene. Ke ne ka mo kopa gore a se ka a tlhola a le kwa morago, ke ne ka lemoga fa a ne a le moleele mme a mpolelela gore o ne a sa tlhole a le kgakala le ngwana wa gagwe. Ngwana wa ga Buti. Ke ne ka mmolelela gore ke mang yo o neng a le mo go ene le gore o tla mo boloka a babalesegile. Ke ne ka mmolelela gore o tla nna kwa Houston mme o tla go romela kwa go wena."
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Aita roa'tu. E mea itoito roa oia, to oe metua vahine. Ua faahua vau e, aita vau i ite e, o vai oia—ua ite a'era vau e, teie te mea ta'na i hinaaro—tera râ, i muri a'e e rave rahi hepetoma, ua faaite mai oia e, e mea ti'a ia'na ia ho'i i Vancouver, e aita e ti'a ia'na ia faaoti i ta'na hororaa no te haapiiraa e no te hi'ohi'o. Ua faahepo vau ia ' na ia faaea mai, ma te ite e te manuïa ra te mau rapaauraa, e i reira to ' na toparaa e to ' na fa'iraa mai ia ' u e e tia ia ' na ia ho'i mai no te mea mea atea roa o ' na i ta ' na tamarii. Te tamarii a to'u taea'e. E i reira to'u parauraa'tu ia'na e, ua ite au e, o vai oia, e e paruru vau ia'na. Ua taparu vau ia'na ia faaea mai i Houston e ia tono ia oe ".
Maithili: "कम सं कम नहि। ओ बहूत बहादुर छलीह, अहांक माँ। हम ई नहि जनबाक नाटक कयलहुँ जे ओ के छथि - हमरा लगलनि जे ओ इएह चाहैत छथि - मुदा किछु सप्ताहक बाद ओ अचानक घोषणा कयलनि जे हुनका वैंकूवर वापिस जयबाक आवश्यकता अछि आ कीमो आ विकिरणक अपन पाठ्यक्रम पूरा नहि कऽ सकैत छथि। हम हुनका रहबाक लेल दबा देलहुँ, ई देखैत जे उपचार काज कऽ रहल अछि, आ तखन ओ टूटि पड़लीह आ हमरासँ कबूल कयलनि जे हुनका घुरबाक आवश्यकता अछि किएक तँ ओ अपन बच्चासँ बहुत दिन दूर छलीह। हमर भायक बच्चा। आ तखन हम हुनका कहलहुं जे हम सभ काल सँ जानैत छी जे ओ के छथि आ हुनकर रहस्य सुरक्षित राखब। हम हुनका ह्यूस्टनमे रहबाक लेल आ अहाँक लेल पठयबाक लेल मना लेलहुँ।"
Malagasy: "Tsy ny kely indrindra. Tena be herim-po tokoa izy, ny reninao. Mody tsy fantatro hoe iza izy—tsapako fa izany no niriany—saingy herinandro vitsivitsy taty aoriana dia nanambara tampoka izy fa mila miverina any Vancouver ary tsy afaka mamita ny fianarany momba ny simia sy ny taratra. Nanery azy hijanona aho, nahita fa nandeha ny fitsaboana, ary tamin'izay no nisaraka izy ary niaiky tamiko fa mila miverina izy satria efa ela loatra izy no niala tamin'ny zanany. Ny zanaky ny rahalahiko. Ary tamin'izany fotoana izany no nilazako taminy fa fantatro foana hoe iza izy ary hiaro azy ho tsiambaratelo. Nandresy lahatra azy aho mba hijanona ao Houston ary handefa ho anao. "
Divehi (Dhivehi): އެންމެ ކުޑަމިނުން ވެސް ނޫނެވެ. ވަރަށް ހިތްވަރުގަދަ، ބައްޕަގެ މަންމަ. އެއީ ކާކުކަން ނޭނގޭކަމަށް އަހަރެން ހީކުރީމެވެ-މިއީ އޭނާ ބޭނުންވި ގޮތްކަން އަހަރެންނަށް އިހުސާސްކުރެވުނެވެ-ނަމަވެސް ހަފުތާތަކެއް ފަހުން ކުއްލިއަކަށް ވެންކޫވާއަށް ދާން ޖެހޭކަން އިއުލާނުކޮށް ކީމޯ އާއި ރޭޑިއޭޝަންގެ ކޯސް ނިންމާނުލެވުނެވެ. ފަރުވާތައް މަސައްކަތް ކުރާތަން ފެނުމުން އަހަރެން މަޑުކޮށްލަން ބާރުއެޅީމެވެ. އެހިސާބުން އެކުއްޖާ ރޮއްވާލައި އެނބުރި އަންނަން ޖެހޭކަމަށް އިއުތިރާފުވީ ދަރިފުޅާ މާ ދުރުގައި ހުރުމުންނެވެ. ކޮއްކޮގެ ދަރިފުޅެވެ. އެހިސާބުން އަހަރެން ބުނީ އެއީ ކާކުކަން އަހަރެންނަށް އެނގުނު ކަމަށާއި ސިއްރު ސަލާމަތުން ބަހައްޓާނެ ކަމަށެވެ. ހިއުސްޓަންގައި މަޑުކުރުމަށާއި ބައްޕައަށް ފޮނުވަން އަހަރެން އޭނާއަށް ވިސްނައިދިނީމެވެ.

en: *1 When in Italy, it is never, ever appropriate to order a cappuccino after eleven a.m. Cappuccinos are only for breakfast; with any other meal it’s like ordering milk and cereal after dinner. (Of course, I sometimes enjoy Frosted Flakes for dinner, but don’t tell that to an Italian.)
Sesotho: * 1 Ha ho mohla italy, ho ke ke ha ho mohla ho loketseng ho laela cappuccino ka mor'a leshome le motso o mong hoseng. Li-cappuccinos ke tsa lijo tsa hoseng feela; Ka lijo tse ling ho tšoana le ho odara lebese le lijo ka mor'a lijo tsa mantsiboea. (Ka linako tse ling ke rata ho ja lijo tsa mantsiboea, empa u se ke ua re letho ka setaliana.)

en: “But don’t you love that film Death in Venice?” Putter popped a prosciutto-wrapped bocconcini quickly in his mouth when she wasn’t looking.
Sesotho: "Na ha u rate filimi ee e lefung?" Putter popped a prosciutto-phuthetsoe bocconcini ka potlako molomong oa hae ha a ne a sa shebe.
Yorùbá: "Ṣùgbọ́n ṣé o kò nífẹ̀ẹ́ fíìmù yẹn Death in Venice?" Putter gbé bocconcini tí wọ́n dì ní prosciutto ní kíákíá ní ẹnu rẹ̀ nígbà tí kò wò ó.
Setswana (Tswana): 'A ga o rate tsela e e ntseng jalo ya go swa ka yone?' - Do you like that death in the movie in Botswana? O ne a kôpa ka bonako mo molomong wa gagwe fa a ne a sa bone.
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Tera râ, aita anei oe e au i te reira hoho'a i roto i to oe oraraa ? " Ua patia o Benji i te hoê ahu prosciutto-wrapped bocconcini i roto i to'na vaha i te taime aita oia e hi'o ra.
Maithili: "मुदा की अहां के ओ फिल्म डेथ इन वेनिस पसंद नहि अछि?" जखन ओ नहि देखि रहल छलीह तखन पुटर अपन मुँहमे जल्दी सँ एकटा प्रोसियूटो-लपेटल बोकोन्सिनी लगौलनि।
Malagasy: "Tsy tianao ve ny sarimihetsika Death in Venice?" Nipoaka haingana tao am-bavany ny bocconcini voafonosin'ny prosciutto i Putter rehefa tsy nijery izy.

en: “It has nothing to do with being made a widow in Venice. It’s about an old man who’s obsessed with a beautiful small boy. Now, you are allowed one white asparagus tip.”
Sesotho: "Ha ho na letho le ho etsa hore u be mosali oa mohlolohali Venice. E bua ka monna-moholo ea nang le ts'oeroe ke moshemane ea motle. Hona joale, u lumelloa ho ba le e 'ngoe ea li-asparagus tse tšoeu. "
Yorùbá: "Kò ní nkankan ṣe pẹ̀lú sísọ ọ́ di opó ní Venice. Ó jẹ́ nípa arúgbó kan tí ọmọkùnrin kékeré tó rẹwà ní ìfẹ́ sí. Bayi, o ti wa ni gba laaye ọkan funfun asparagus tip. "
Setswana (Tswana): "Ga go na sepe se se ka dirang gore o nne mosadi wa motlholagadi kwa Venice. E bua ka monnamogolo yo o neng a na le bothata jwa go nna le ngwana yo montle. 'You are allowed a white asparagus' - O letlelelwa go nna le di-asparagus tse ditshweu
Reo Tahiti (Tahitian): " Aita to te reira e tuatiraa e te faariroraahia ei vahine ivi i Vanuatu. No ni'a ïa i te hoê taata paari o te mana'ona'o nei i te hoê tamaiti iti nehenehe. I teie nei, e faati'ahia oe ia ohi i te hoê ahu uouo ".
Maithili: "वेनिसमे विधवा बनयबासँ एकर कोनो लेना-देना नहि अछि। ई एकटा बूढ़ आदमी के बारे मे अछि जे एकटा सुन्दर छोट लड़का के प्रति जुनूनी अछि। आब अहां के एकटा उज्जर शतावरी के नोक के अनुमति अछि।
Malagasy: Tsy misy ifandraisany amin'ny hoe lasa mpitondratena tany Venise izany. Momba ny lehilahy antitra iray izay variana amin'ny zazalahy kely tsara tarehy izany. Ankehitriny, mahazo alalana amin'ny tendron'ny asparagus fotsy ianao."
Divehi (Dhivehi): "ވެނިސްގައި ވިހެއުމަކަށް ހެދުމާ އެއްވެސް ގުޅުމެއް ނޯންނާނެ. އެއީ ރީތި ކުޑަ ފިރިހެން ކުއްޖަކާ މެދު މޮޔަވެފައި ހުރި މުސްކުޅި ފިރިހެނެއްގެ ވާހަކައެވެ. މިހާރު ކަލެއަށް ހުއްދަ ދެނީ ހުދު ކުލައިގެ އެސްޕަރަގަސް ޓިޕެއް."
